\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \fi-461\li461\ri0\sa240\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin461\itap0\pararsid7233595 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 The well brought up people are horrible. They're not the real gentry, they're very grateful for have - someone to help them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 They showed you appreciation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
Oh they did. Lady Lawrence said to me one day - she said, nurse, she said - we couldn't do without you. You're greatest help to us. They appreciated you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 You knew you were valued?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
Yes. Different altogether - when I hear people talk about their nurse down to children, a little old general, well that's - no thank you. You're - you had to do this and that - to do that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yours was quite a different order of work a together wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
Not many people - in this town I don't suppose know much about gentry and - not like I did. I was well mixed up with the - Lord and Lady Davy, they were relations, and we used to stay with them. They had got a big - estate and they had
 - footmen. The house of servants, we used to go and stay there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Was that in Melton Mowbray too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No. That was - can't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Somewhere further afied anyway?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes. Can't remember now what - where that place was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 When you went to stay did they take any of their other servants as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Just you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 The nurse and the children went with them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 What about the ladies maid?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh yes, she'd go too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 But nobody else?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No one else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 The others stayed behind?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 When you got to the new house where you were visiting, did you have rooms there again?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes. Yes, you generally did. Oh I remember when I was with the Troutbecks we used to go and stay at Hazelmere. And - oh and round there, t
hat's really where Connan Doyle, around there. And we used to go into their - walks all round in the fields there. All woods. Connan Doyle - some of his books were written about that. I remember there were all there dilberries growing low down, these litt
l
e black things. And - I was walking and there was an old snake jumped up. And I flew out of that place, I never wanted to go there anymore. But that was awfully wooded all round there. And I always think when I think and hear about him - on his - in his s
ome of his woods that he used to talk about.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 So at the Troutbecks were three children and at the Lawrence's there were also three?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Both time you had the three to look after?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Well - of course there's - lots of things I've forgotten.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 But you remember a lot about those times don't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 How your work was organized?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh yes, I - the work and that never leave me because I - I know we - was happy enough. Easy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10880908\charrsid6895608 Do you ever wis}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 h you could have had another job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
No, I was quite content. Because in those times the jobs were - rough and - and I mean the small jobs were nothing. All these big houses, they kept - enough servants, and you had good food. I think that's the upbringing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Can you remember what money you got for your first job?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Well I know I only had twenty-four pounds a year. And food. That wasn't high wages but still - it was good -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 It was better than a lot of the others got though wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh yes. I don't know what they got. But I - I remember that's what my wage was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you send any home or did you keep it yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
Oh - I used to send home - presents to mother. And I used to send home a lot of childrens clothes, because - the - the children there didn't wear 
their clothes too hard and when they were tired of them I used to send my mother - the clothes. And my sisters had them and they were quite good - a lot of clothes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you get twenty-four pounds all the years you were there or did it go up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No. No different.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 When you left did you get any more or did you get just the same?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 When I left - I didn't get - ever get more than that anywhere.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 How did you get the job with Lady Lawrence, did she advertise?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 One lady told another. Recommended. Yes. Yes. I never had - I never had -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 To go to a registry office or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No. No. No. Well I must have been all right I think else I wouldn't have had the recommendation.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 When you first went to Lady Lawrence was the nurse she already had still there, did she tell you about the job and everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
Yes, I - yes, she told me about Lady - Lady Lawrence. Friends, they meet yousee. 'Cos Ladies, they go afternoon and have cups of tea and meet - meet different friends and talk their businesses over. And then that's how I got recommended you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 When you went to Lady Lawrence's house for the first time, who told you about your duties and your work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Because it was just the same you mean?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Just the same. 
Just - you're just shown into your rooms and your bedroom and that, then - and introduced to the children - and then you - you're left - to carry on.;
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 And they just left it all to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes. Nothing you - not - no orders at all. Unless they want 
- to do anything or - take - take you anywhere or - anyone to call and see the children. That's all. No, they never tell you what to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 What about the nurse who had been there before you, was she still there to hand over to you or had she gone already?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
I think she'd gone. Yes, I think they'd gone, 'cos I think they don't often - keeping one to tell the other. I think they leave you to do - carry on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 The very first house you went to was near the Troutbecks was it, when you first went up in the holidays to help your aunt?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh - before I went altogether. I can't remember the houses very well now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Was there more than one that you went to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes. There - you see, I went to either of them. And - when I was first under nurse I went to
 Ireland to the one - who lived in Ireland. That's where I had me training really. See.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 How long were you trained for then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 I was there two years and a half.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 That was before the Troutbecks?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes. Before I went on my own that was, when I was training to be -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Like your apprenticeship?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes. I was trained under - and she was very strict. I had to do all the work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 You mean cleaning up and that kind of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 What family was that, do you remember, were they an Irish family?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
Now I've got mixed up, they were the Lawrences and the others were the Yates. The last people were - Yates. And the other was - was Sir Charles and - and oh well I went to Ireland but I - to be trained. And I - I can remember
 going out there by the boat and everything. And I was with Lady Lawrence when she had her second baby. She was a great horsewoman. And - Lady Lawrence that was. And - Sir Charles - he was in the Army I think. And they lived at Welgard Castle, Dublin. A l
o
vely place. And I can tell you that - all that, they were - poor Irish were terrible people. Poor. There was a lodge gate about three miles round this house, one at the front and one at the back. And my aunt was head nurse to this - Lady that had one chil
d
, when the second come you see, I went. And - we had a nice - a nice house, nice rooms and that. But when I went I was so frightened of the Irish people, they had their own laundry and - everything and their own gardens. When I went down to take the - the
 
washing one day, these girls spoke so funny - looked so scared, I did - I half acraid of them. They're a funny lot. Very poor. And in the garden latterly - there used to be an old lady come - old women had to work in the gardens. Women, and they're so har
d
 up and - and poor. They were allowed to have our leavings off the table and every other - every day we went and took something in the garden to - to leave. The Irish were very very poor. And - the houses, when we went down to the lodge gates, they lived 
on potatoes. They had no meat. They were all Catholics, Roman Catholics. And they always had to say mass - say their prayers every day and - and - give so much to the church. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 You'd never met people like that before I suppose?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh no, I was f
rightened of half them, they were frightful people. And when I got to go round visiting some of the houses - they - they houses was that poor they'd got bare floors, stone floors. And - next to the doors old shed where they'd got - donkeys and horses in. 
Next door. And they only had two rooms to live in. And no - and no carpets. Terrible.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Why did you have to visit the houses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 I don't know, I think I used to have to - call on something, take them something at times.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Because they were so poor?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
Yes. But I can remember, that never leaves me, those horrible - places. Some of them were - somebody was ill I think there. And In a bedroom with no carpet, all bare floors and - and - one room like I might have a bedroom off there. All just the two
 rooms. And - then outside there was - chickens and all that running about. Terrible.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 What sort of clothes did they wear, the children wear?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 I didn't see many children, not where I lived. The - the parents were bad enough, they hadn't got much 
to live, very very poor. I always think of them now as like a poor race. There must be a lot of poor - well I stayed two years and a half and - we - we went to - the sea in the summer. And I enjoyed that, I used to get up every morning and have a - run th
e sea and have a bathe. Lovely. And - that was very nice there. And that's lovely country.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did they have a lot of servants in the house there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes, well - I forget about the servants in that house. I was - I think they had a butler and they didn'
t have so many servants there. But - it was a - an old - a big old house. With two drives to it. And of course they had all - every - the food was good and everything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did the children also go down in the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes, just about the same. The children were treated just the same, went down in the drawing room. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 What about the baby, did the baby go down?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Not much. Not the babies when they're young. But - the baby that was born that time when I was - was very restless child. Cried a
 lot. She was a great horsewoman and they reckon that she did too much with the horseriding that that affected the child. And for a long time it was awfully - restless child. And my aunt - used to have awful job with it. Never sleep you know, always on th
e
 go, always fidgeting. Well I stayed two years and a half because - and I got rather tired of being in Ireland. I gave - I gave it up. Because I didn't like being out there so long. Then I came home and had a holiday. And then I got - that's when I first 
took my first place.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you get the Troutbecks from recommendation from those people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 I forget where I got that recommendation. No, not from them. I got it from - through my aunts. Those were at London, through some of them.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Was that baby fed on bottles, it wasn't breast fed I suppose?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Bottle fed baby.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 The mother didn't feed it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
No. She was a - very excitable woman. Yes. I - and I - I - well I didn't see much of her. He - the gentleman, he was away in the Army you see, he was Army man.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 In the other houses did the fathers ever come up to the nursery?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Not a lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did they occasionally or not at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Troutbecks - well he was at work you see. But - with the Troutbecks we went away and of course went to the s
easide and - and - then they used - we had - more mixed up then. And used to go out with - walks with them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 In a group together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 It must have been very interesting, all the places you saw and the people you met?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 When you met your husband how did you actually meet him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
Well there was a - there was a sort of a - fete on at Ashford - at - Assfordbury. And there was a - all sorts of show, like vegetable shows and that. He went there as a head gardner from - from Craven Lodge. To judge - he went judging the show. Yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 And that's where you met him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
Yes. And they were dancing a polka there, you know, music. And he came up to - he was watching, he came up to me and asked me if I'd dance. I said, I can't dance much, I've never - only a polka. And that started it. And I knew his brothers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 How did you know his brothers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Well - I'd met them in London. They - yes, his brothers used to go and do dinner parties. You know, they used to hire - certain people 
and his brothers used to go - round helping at these dinner parties, waiting on and that. So much a night I suppose. And I'd met the brother - at one of our parties. And when I saw him - that bought us together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 How did you manage to see him after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
I told the Lady. I told - Mrs Troutbeck. No, not Troutbecks - Lady Yates. I'd met someone and I'd - I'd like to go out some evenings to meet him. And we did have some evenings too, we got soaking wet one night when I was out. Poured and poured and
 - and he'd got to go - he'd got to go - where - yes, it was in - it was Asbury where the fete was - he'd got to go back to - to Melton Mowbray, all in the wet. He went drenching wet and I went home and I - I had to take all my clothes off and have a bath
. And no one knew anything about it. And then I - he used to come over so often and she used to let me go out and meet him. And then eventually when I told her I was getting }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15757198 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 , she said, well, she said, I do hope you haven't made a mistake and you'll be happy. So - I said, no, I shall be all right. And of course I }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15757198 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608  him and - left them. And she gave me that silver teapot.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 And you'd known him about six months had you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes. Six months. And he'd got a sister who was getting }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15757198 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608  who was looking after him. So we got }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15757198 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
 and my people - my mother and father never met 'til they came down to be }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15757198 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 You }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15757198 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608  from home?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes, I came home. Yes. I was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15757198 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608  in St Marys church here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you have a honeymoon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 I
 forget. Yes. I went out to - out to - stay with with my brother over at Goldhangar. And stayed there for about a fortnight and then we went - I went back to my own house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 That was at Craven Lodge was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 What was the house like?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
Oh it was quite nice, there was a - two larger rooms than these and a - a small - a little kitchen. And - two good sized bedrooms and a small bedroom. It was not a bad - in fact, the carpet that I had down there was too big for this one here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you have your own garden there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
Oh well I had the - all - plenty of garden. 'Cos it was all open there, I could walk round the gardens and - beautiful gardens they had. Yes. And the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you have any of your own where you could plant flowers if you'd wanted to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No, I didn't have anything. Not - not my own, my husband did all that. His men you see, they planted all that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did he have people under him there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh yes. He had - big green - greenhouses, there were peaches and grapes and all that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did he like his work or would he have rather have done something else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
Oh he liked his work, he'd been brought up to that. He was trained with the - Rothchild people. Of Rothbay. And he - they had what they called bothies in there
. Places where they lived and they had woman to look after 'em and that. Oh they were trained properly. Bothy, yes. Yes, that was what they called them. Room - they'd have men there, they'd be trained for gardening, and the head gardener would train these
 men and they'd put on different - departments. One'd do one thing and one'd do another, another od - my husband did more greenhouse work than anything else. And flowers and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you get vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh yes. When he went on his own you see, h
e went to Craven Lodge, with a Colonel Boldop he was. And he had of course a nice house and - big grouns and horses and everything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 And this is the house that you went to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 You joined him there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes. And I stayed seven years. And 
the Colonel died and lady - well she went to London and - and one thing and another and we got tired of being there so we give it up. Then we went to London for a bit, had a rest. Stored our furniture. And - went to the Isle of Wight of two years. Yes. Th
at was very nice. Oh I had a nice time there. But we didn't like the lady much and we gave it up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Why didn't you like her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 She - she was rather a nigger driver. She was - and she didn't - didn't like me having visitors staying. Very funny. They'r
e funny - people, so we just gave up and came to Colchester. Brought all furniture here and then - we went to - Lexdon Park for a time. Just - he was gardener there, Lexdon Park, and - they had a - funny house there to live in. Cold horrible house, great 
old rooms and - just ordinary fireplace, we used to sit with our coats on there. Well we didn't stay long. 'Til the - the Castle Park was going and my husband got it you see. Yes. So then we were there ten years in the Castle Park.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 When you were at Craven Lodge did you have any work to do yourself or did you work just in your own home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
Only my home. I never did - no, no. Never did anything. I had all the vegetables and fruit I wanted. One year - we had too many peaches, I - I turned it all into j
am. Peaches, peaches, peaches. They never taste how they - they don't taste - what ones like I used to have.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you make bread there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you make anything else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh jams and - pickles and all that. Oh yes, I used to cook.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did your husband come home for dinner midday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh he was on the place you see. Come in when he liked.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 So you saw quite a lot of him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh yes, and he was in the choir - Sundays. And then we joined a mission, little mission church, as a scho
olmaster there and we used to have little services. And - and then we gave teaparties, we had a big do Christmastime. And I had some - I - had a - table and I used to find everything and invite so many people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 At Craven Lodge, the actual house, did they have any parties for the people who worked there or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No. No. They didn't give any parties.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did they give you anything at Christmastime or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 I think they gave my husband a little present. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 They didn't give you anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
Not a lot. No. I think - they were - they weren't really like - the people I'd lived with in the nursery. Not that sort. No. I think they were more jumped up people. He was in then - in the Army. And she was a rather - highty-toity
 woman, I don't think she could have been born - not aristocrat. Not the same. She was always nice to me. But I never did any work. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did they ever ask you to?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No. No, they had somebody else go in the house. They had their maids there, I don'
t know half of them. 'Cos that was a fairly big place. I don't know how many bedrooms they had.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Thinking of the gentry and the aristocrats you hadn't met those sort of people round in Colchester at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 I don't - no, these are all retired people
 here. And they're business people. They've no - there's no one got the house - not really. Out of the town there might have been some, like - Lower Marney Towers and - those big places, they might have a - big staff of servants in those places. But not -
 not in Colchester.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 What did your mother and father think about the gentry and people like that? Did they feel the same say as you about them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Well they never spoke about, they knew I was all right. I don't think they bothered about - they knew I was happy and - when I }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15757198 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608  they liked my husband - and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did they ever meet the people you worked for at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes, she came up and had - she came up to London with my sister. One of my sister's suffered with the eyes and she took her to the
 hospital there in London and she came up and had the meals there with me for the day. Oh yes, the lady met - Lady - yes, Mrs Troutbeck. That time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you ever remember if you ever left anything what your mother said?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh we didn't. We cleared it all up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Do you remember if there were certain things you didn't like, there was nothing you didn't like?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Could you bring a toy or a book t- the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Read at the table - no, we had to have our food and - nothing else. No reading at table, not my father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 And no toys at table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
Oh we had - always had - proper laid table. We weren't allowed running about eating like some children are today. Oh no, it was all proper meals. Got ready and we all sat down together and got our
s together. And father went off to work and the rest of us went off to school.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 That was dinnertime?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did your mother put the food from the cooking pot onto the place or did she put them in dishes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No, we had dishes on our table always. Never pots or anything. We were trained properly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Was your main meal midday dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes, always a good main dinner. Pudding of some sort, meat and a sweet generally after of some sort.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you start with a pudding?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Sometimes th
ey'd start with Yorkshire pudding and gravy alone. Like children like it. And then have the meat after and then have a rice pudding and apples or something else like - just today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 And vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh yes. Always two vegetables. And grew them out of the garden.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you have potatoes every day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh yes, potatoes and - whatever were in season we had.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Potatoes and one other vegetables you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh yes. Carrots. Onions. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you drink at midday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No. Never at middle day. No, we had - we - we had - if we want a drink we got up and had it afterwards.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Not on the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No. We didn't drink water much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 What did you have for breakfast in those days?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Porridge. Real old fashioned porridge, Scotts porridge. And eggs. Just the same, eggs and bacon like we have today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Every day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes. Ham was the same, better than it is today. Ever so much better. Meat was better than what it is today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Do you always have breakfast together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Your father had gone already had he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
Well if it - we were - had - he was home at eight and we all sat down about eight o'clock and had breakfast together, then the children would say their graces and off they'd go and then father would go when he was
 ready. And he had to walk. Even though - he had a bicycle later but - he used to walk, right from Gray Road down to - well, it wasn't very far, down the High Street to Moffats where it was in Culver Street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 So he didn't have to go work before breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes, he used to go at six o'clock in the morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 He came back for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes, they'd start at six o'clock those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Then he'd come home again for dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes. And then he was home - I think it was about - whether they
 - about six o'clock I believe they always worked 'til. I forget about that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Then he'd come home then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes. Sometimes though - worked 'til eight when they were busy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Would he go back then after tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No, he - he'd take something and then he'd - he'd have his tea there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did he have tea with you in the afternoon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
If he was home he would. Oh we had our meals together when he was home, there was no rubbing about with cups in your hand and all that sort of thing. Oh we always had to sit at table.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you say grace at all the meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Generally. Oh yes, well father - well they weren't hard - people, but they had their discipline. Which there isn't today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 On a Sunday was the food different, you say you got the joint?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
Oh yes, we always had a - lovely joint on Sunday and a - nice Yorkshire pudding. Sometimes a boiled one, sometimes a - a baked one. And - that dinner was the best of the week really because - we'd have odds and ends in the week, mince puddings and - a
nd different stews and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you have anything different at Sunday teatime?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Very often we did, extra tea. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 What sort of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh we'd have - a tin of - fish of some sort, salmon or something. Cakes, mother always made all - 
all her own. There were - she didn't buy any.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did she make bread too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did she make jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh yes. Made plenty of jam. All preserves she could.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Any pickles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes, pickles. I used to - but I don't now for myself because I don't eat them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 What about beer and wine, did she make that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No, no. No. I don't think ever made beer or wine. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Do you remember if she made any medicines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh only - only - sugar and vinegar - when we'd got - sore throat or cold and -
 hadn't a - butter and sugar, little things and sugar and butter on a plate, to ease the throat. And then she'd put on - plasters on your chest if you got any chesty - tallow plasters on brown - on paper - brown paper I think it was. I remember that. Oh y
es. But I don't get chest on - I'm notchesty.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 What about tinne meat, do you remember tinned meat when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Only tinned salmon.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Corned beef?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Corned beef was ordinary. Like - you buy it now - plain. And pork and that, home 
cured pork was the rage, there was a shop in Crouch Street where they used to cure their own pork and we - sweet - what they called sweet pickle, and that was lovely pork. Different to what you get today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 What about rabbit, did you ever get rabbit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh yes, there was rabbits all right but I wouldn't eat them now. I don't fancy them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you buy them or did your father go and shoot them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh - bought them. My - my father didn't shoot. He did no shooting.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you ever get any from people in Goldhangar, your people there at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Well I think occasionally you would get one sometimes and - from a shop.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 But not given to you buy people who'd shot them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No. No. Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Do you ever remember seeing your mother having less food so that you could have more or was there no shortage of food in your family?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No, there was always enough food. If the money went round I suppose.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 You don't remember seeing your mother having less?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No. No, but she was careful. She was 
careful but she never was without - of course there was a lot of poverty in my time. And - a lot of children were very ragged and - had poor shoes and I've seen - used to see them. But I think we must have been a little different.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Your father was a skilled man and a foreman wasn't he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did any of the ragged children go to your school?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
Oh yes, we all went to the public school. You see - there was a school down priory Street where we had to go. Of course that's all done away with years ago.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 What was that called?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Very good teachers there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Was that a Church of England school or a board school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 I think it was all - not - nothing. I should say ordinary school by - run - I don't know whether it was run with the town 
or not, I don't know that. There was very good teachers there. And believe their name were Rolfe. And they were splendid teachers and well organized.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Were there just two teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh - there was a - well, several teachers, I forget a lot about s
chool. I only know we had slates then. To write on. And when we had books we had to write a certain way. Copy books. But - then and when I was older we did cooking and then we sold the stuff and took it home. We had - when this gas came in we had cooking 
classes. Yes. Made cakes and things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you go to just the one school or did you go to another school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
Well - I was silly. I went to the one and then - my neighbour - had a daughter and she went to a private school. And of course I talked my mot
her round, let me go there, finishing off, but I didn't learn a thing, I knew as much about it as the governess did. I never improved myself there, I taught her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 How old were you when you went there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 I forget. About two years I was there and I think we paid sixpence a week there, for that schooling. Private school that was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Was that just girls or girls and boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Girls.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Do you know how old you were when you left there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 I should think we left about fourteen. We weren't compell
ed to stay on in those days. About fifteen you see I reckon. And then you see I went away - altogether, sixteen. And then I never was home anymore. Only holidays and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 When you were at the private school was there just the one governess?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes, the one person taught. I suppose was a - educated woman and - took it up and just taught the girls.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 But you felt she didn't have anything to teach you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh no, I knew as much as she did. I know I never learnt a thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 What did you think of her, did you like her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
Oh it was nice going to a private school 'cos you felt you were a little more - you know, a little ahead of the ordinary going to private school then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you have a uniform?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No. Just ordinary.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Were the children a different class of children from the other school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
Well they were a little better off you see, well clad, we weren't raggedy. When you went to the other childrens' schools they weren't too clean. You see you caught - my mother had to comb our heads every night. Every - when we were young.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you catch things there then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
Oh yes. Caught them, they'd come from - dirty children. All that sort of thing, you had to wash - and not only fleas you caught. In those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did the teacher always treat all the children the same or did they single out some children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 I think we had different teachers occasionally, on different subjects.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 How did the teachers treat the children who came from the poor homes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Always the same, no differe
nt. No, there was no distinction. I never found any distinction. Only always felt sorry for the poor little things who went half washed and raggedy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did they mix in with the rest of you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Or did they keep to themselves?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh no, they mixed up, the children didn't trouble 'cos there was too many of them. You know, in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did the teachers emphasi}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11762404\charrsid6895608 z}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 e things as important then in the public school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Well they just taught you - ordinary things you see, just plain - ordinary things, there was nothing special.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 What about in behaviour?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh you had to behave. They had a cane in those days. Children weren't taking notice or weren't doing it they got a rap on the fingers.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you ever get that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No. We're 
not supposed to talk you see - listen. If they catch you whispering, you - one'd see it - the teacher see it - they were so strict.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did they cane the girls as well as the boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh they'd cane anybody. You had to - you had to be artful.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 When you started school did you walk there on your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh yes, we had no buses. And no - nothing to go - no bicycles in those days. Not like they - they - not for children or anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 How long did it take you to walk to Priory Street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 I neve
r remember, we used to just go off and take our dinners with us. In the wintertime. Well we generally did because we couldn't get home in the time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 So when you had your midday dinner with your father it would be mostly in the holidays would it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Holidays, we only had holidays - go out for the day anywhere, we didn't - have any go away business.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 You wouldn't stay away?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No. Not in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 You didn't ever go and stay with a relation or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Sometimes I did. Yes, we used to - some of us used to go and stay with relations.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 You said you used to like to go to Goldhangar?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes. I used to go quite a lot when I was young. Well then mother had the babies, she couldn't go so - I used to go with - and stay wit
h my grandfather and grandmother. And - during the holidays. Yes I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Do you ever remember having tinned vegetables or fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No. No tinned - no tinned vegetables in those times and no tinned rice. Nothing like that. Plain good rice, better th
an what we're getting now I think. I think that today's harder.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 And the fruit, was that tinned?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh plenty of fruit, no tinned - not much, no. No tinned fruit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 When grown ups were talking were you allowed to join in the conversation when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 When parents were talking? Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 You could join in the conversation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh yes. Oh my - we were never put in another room, we always did the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 And you could talk to the grown ups?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh yes. Oh yes. Talk to the grown ups.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Do you remember if your parents said you should hit back if other children hit you, or didn't that happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh no. No. No. My father was against fighting with the boys or anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did anybody ever bully you at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No, I don't think I - I think I got very fair - I don't remember - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 What kind of people do you think your parents hoped you would grow up to be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Well, they just wanted us to be ordinary - good citizens I think. Give - they gave us the best they coul
d and then we were ready to go out in the world we went out what we wanted to do. The boys were educated - under my father at his works there. And they all got good jobs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Were they all apprenticed?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh - well they were taken in and given a little money probably you see. And - they all turned out good - pattern makers and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 What did your parents thing about swearing in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Swearing? No, my father wouldn't swear. No - no, he wouldn't have bad language. We weren't brought up like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 I wonder if you picked it up outside?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No. Oh you didn't hear it much in those days. No. Very little swearing. Oh no, nothing like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 There's more today perhaps of that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh I think it's worse today, I think everything is w
orse. I think home life in those days - were natural and good. People - children were brought up - with clear minds and - they - brought up to work to get their living. And not to be pampered with. To give them everything they want today they get don't th
ey.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 If you had any worries could you share them with your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh yes, always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you have any worries as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No. I didn't have any worries or anything - no, the only thing, some Sundays when I was a girl - I would go out for 
a walk and I used to meet - some boys and - I used to go on the Abbey Fields for walks with one or two friends and - we - used to meet a few boys and have a chat. And I know - they were photographers son that used to meet us so one day somebody told my fa
ther and then he teased me about it. But he didn't mind as long as we were not doing anything wrong. But he was strict about boys and going out - I never was allowed out at nights. Oh no. Not in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 What time did you have to be in then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Never went out in the evenings, there was nowhere to go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 You could go for a walk with boys though in the afternoon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh when there was light. But not when there's dark. Oh no. Father never allowed us go on the rounds walking about with boys. No, w
e weren't allowed to mix with boys like they are today. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you bring those boys home?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
Oh no. No, we just knew them. My father - at the time when I had a young man I was over twenty then and he didn't like me taking him home. Oh no, they were strict on that sort of thing. There wasn't - the wrong goings on like there is today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 But couldn't you go out even in the summer evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh yes, you could go out, we all went for walks and that. In the summer. Oh yes, we all went out for walks together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 You mean the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 All together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 In that house in Gray Road there were four bedrooms?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Four bedrooms.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Before you went away to service how did the family use those rooms?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Well - you see - I had - there was 
four brothers you see. Yes, there were four brothers. Well - two slept in one room. One slept in the other. Oh they - they - they were divided out. And I had one room to myself. Yes. 'Cos I was the only girl then - for a time. Well then I went away, of co
urse mother had the other children - afterwards, more or less.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 So your parents had a room to themselves too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh yes, we had - we were just - always had -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Enough room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes, we never - never crushed in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did your brothers share a bed or did they have beds of their own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh shared beds. Shared double - double beds then. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Would you say that the ideas you got about how to behave - You say she did show affection to her children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes. She was brought up, she was the you
ngest of a - her family, my mother. And she had - two sisters and one brother. One brother was - went - as a - soldier and he was a Sergeant or Sergeant-Major I believe in the Army, and then my two aunts went as nurses you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 They never }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15757198 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No. Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Do you remember how your mother and father liked you to behave towards your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh we were very - very happy, we - didn't quarrel. No. The brothers were very - brought up ordinary and they went and played and - e
njoyed themselves. And they were brought up to come in and wash themselves before their meals and - we were brought up - quite tidy really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Can you remember when you had a birthday would it be different from an ordinary day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh, more or less. Mother would make us a cake. And we'd get perhaps a few pence and - like that. But nothing like it is today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 What about guests, did you have a friend in to tea or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh yes, we had parties. Oh yes, we had birthday parties.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Can you tell me what you would do at the party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
Well we'd play games amongst ourselves, sort of amusing ourselves and the boys, they had a cellar this house, they'd go down and play with their engines they had - engines they had lit with methylated spi
rits, they run them - with that. And - they'd be down in the cellar playing with their toys and we'd be perhaps playing with our dolls, and I had dolls in those times and they lasted years, these dolls. Wooden dolls some of them. First doll.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you have a china doll too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Then afterwards I had a better doll. Afterwards. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you play games like oranges and lemons and that type of game?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh yes. Yes. They were all those games, orange and lemons. And then we had bowls - you know, w
e had hoops in those days. The men - the boys had iron - iron ones, with an iron thing they ran along with that on a - with an iron thing on. And girls, we had a lot of hoops. And tops. Games with tops you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you have hoops like the boys or were they different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Wooden ones. Yes, wooden - wooden hoops.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did girls play marbles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Not a great deal. Boys did. No, girls didn't mess about with gutters in the road so much, not - not - no. Not then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 What about skipping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh skipping, yes, skipping ropes, oh yes, we skipped.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Do you remember people skipping in Colchester at the Castle Park or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 I don't remember - no, not in my time - much about the Castle Park, I think it was - must have been rough in my time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Was it rather rough round there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
I think so. 'Course this is only latter years that was cleared up and - yes, of course - what I remember the Castle Park the - the - they fought a duel almost in there didn't they. Yes. So it was - must have been rough.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 At parties were there any other games you played, did you play postman's knock and those kind of games?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh yes, we played that. And we used to dress up, as children, and go round and knock at the mother's - at the front door. We were very 
fond of dressing up in clothes. I think like they do today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you have some clothes that you were allowed just to dress up in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh yes - some old clothes and we used to put them on and - walk round. And in my time there were three - women calle
d Silly Anna's, they were - I don't know where they came from but they used to walk the streets, they had big hats and long clothes, they used to go from door to door begging. Silly Annas they were called. And I - they used to walk round Gray Road and all
 round those roads every other day. And they lived down somewhere in the Maldon Road in a little place. And they used to go from house to house - begging for food.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 What did your mother do when they came?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh we always used to give them something. Within reason.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 They didn't ask for money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Sometimes we - more or less - they - wanted food.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Were there beggars in the street in those days?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Can't remember. About beggars. But I remember the Silly Annas.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Were there gypsies around then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No, I don't - I don't remember many gypsies then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you have a newspaper, a daily paper or anything when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 I think there's papers - newspaper. I think there must have been newspapers in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you have them in your family every day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 I can't remember. I can't remember. I think father used to have newspapers. Whether every day or only weekends I couldn't say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you have books?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh yes, books to read. Yes. But there was no libraries then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 What books did you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
I had - different - when we had birthdays and sometimes we've had different fairy stories you know, old fashioned fairy stories. When I hear them I now I remember some of them. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did your mother ever read to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh yes. She used to sit by the fire and sing and read to us. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did she read to herself in the evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No, she didn't have time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Was she mending in the evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Always doing some sewing or something, 'cos she made - a lot of the childrens' clothes, the babies' clothes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Do you remember your father reading?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Well - I forget about him. I think he was in the garden, what I remember. He was more fond of gardening.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Of course they went to bed earlier then didn't they?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh yes. 'Cos they had to get up at six o'clock of a morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 What about Christmas Day when you were a girl?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh we - we used to hang our stockings up. And we used to have - orange and - those fancy pigs, coloured pigs, all odds and
 ends in there, never very big presents, but we all had our stockings hung up and - we always had something in them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you have a Christmas tree or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Sometimes we did. When the children were little they had a Christmas tree. Oh we had a very good Christmas.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you get together with other relatives or friends at Christmas time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
Yes, generally and - yes. I know my aunt that lived - lived in Rolston Road, she used to come to Gray Road and stay there and the children, we all used to 
meet, there were three or four of them. And - then they got late and then they all got tired. 'Cos I was older you see, the younger ones had got tired. And they put 'em to bed - put 'em - the girls at the top and the boys at the bottom. In the double beds
, the young children, they got tired. So they - they all stopped the night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 That was at your aunt's house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
Yes. Our house. Yes. The boys in one bed and the girls in another, you know, and if there wasn't room, top to bottom, like that. So that I - I can remember that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did she always come to you at Christmastime quite regularly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh we used to go them occasionally. Only they hadn't got such a big a house, I think we had the biggest house at that time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Four bedrooms was quite a lot then wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh yes, those houses still stand. 'Cos they're very old now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Do you remember a family funeral at all before 1919?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Funerals? No, I don't remember the - no, I was - the little ones, I was away I think. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 You don't remember a funeral up to the end of the first war?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No. But they were - all buried - buried in the cemetery. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 When you were a child were you ever taken out shopping to buy things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Not a great deal. I forget about - going shopping with mothe
r when I was young. I remember going getting as we were older, going to shops - in Crouch Street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you shop for her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh yes. We used to go shopping. But - I can't remember a lot of shopping. That didn't appeal me I don't think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Was Guntons there in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 I couldn't say that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Do you remember, you used to go and see a couple at Fordham Heath didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Then you had your aunts, were there any other friends and relations you used to be taken to see?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 We 
had a - uncle - somewhere on the New Town way - now we used to go up sometimes. He had no family. Yes, my - my father's brother, we used to go there sometimes. But my aunt was so houseproud I remember, we mustn't do this and mustn't do that. We didn't lik
e going. No. There was nothing to do when we went to them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 When your father took you out and you used to go and have a walk round the Leather Bottle up there did your mother come too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh no, she stayed at home, cooked the dinner. See - it was on 
Sunday when she was cooking the dinner. Otherwise we had walks with mother - we used to go on the Abbey Field a lot. And at that time there was - there were very good Regiments in Colchester. And there was Scotch Regiment and I remember going up in the mo
rning to see the parades, and they had beautiful parades. The bands playing and - marching you know, Scotch Guards. I remember that quite well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you enjoy that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes. All the - lots of people used to go up to see them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Do you remember going to any plays or anything like that, any entertainments in a hall?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 I don't remember a lot of plays when I was little. No. There were - I don't think there were many plays when I was little. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Any circuses or travelling shows or anything while you were at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 I think there were circuses. But I don't think - we weren't allowed to go alone. No, my father didn't care for them much. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Do you remember if you went out on Bank Holidays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh we used to go to Clacton for the day. 
Yes. Had to go by train then. And we used to take our food with us and all sit on the beach and - and have quite a good time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you go on the pier?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No, not much with - not several children. There - there was nothing - we used to play on the beach all the time. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you go there by train?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes. Train there and back.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 At the weekends did you have a job to do on a Saturday or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes, we had work to do. I had - always had to help mother with - cleaning up an
d making the beds. The boys had to do - all the boots and shoes for the weekend and Sundays you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you have any job to do earning money on a Saturday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Generally clean knives and forks.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 You got some money for that did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Well about tuppence or so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 From your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Or father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 You didn't do anything for neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh no. No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 What was Sunday like then when you were children?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh we had to get up and put all clean clothes on and go to church, Sunday school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 That was Church of England was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
Yes. And we had to go right down to St Botolphs church at first. We belonged to that. And - I remember - going in a hall there, we had - didn't go to the church, we had a hall and had a nice S
unday and then we walked home for dinner afterwards. That was the beginning. And then when they got older the boys got to St Marys church, two of them were in the choir and then the other younger sisters I remember - they all went to St.Marys, after I was
 away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Were you in the choir at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Not then. No. I didn't go to any choir - 'til - after we came back, to Colchester to live.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Then you joined a choir did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes, in Lexden.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 And your husband too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes. Yes. Yes, else - my husband was in the Melton Mowbray choir all the time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 You were in the church choir at Lexden?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Do you know if St Botolphs church had a temperance a club, a Band of Hope or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 There was something of that but I can't remember much about that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 You didn't join in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 I don't think I did, I think - I think my brothers did. They - they were in more after I left home you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Before you left home did you belong to any clubs connected with the church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No. No. No. No, but I remember before I went away though I was at - I went in and helped teach the children, the young ones, Sunday.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes. Oh I love children. I used to go -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 You liked teaching?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes. I went as a teacher temporary 'til - I left you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Had you gone to Sunday school yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Was that in the afternoon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Service in the morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 And school in the afternoon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 You didn't go again in the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Twice a day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No. Well - we had singing evenings you see, piano. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 That must have been so nice?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes. Father sang, he was a very good alto. And I used to play the hymns then. Mother didn't sing much 
but - she enjoyed it, we all joined in. We used to have nice Sunday evening. Oh there's no home - home life with the youngs ones. Not like there was with the older people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Were you taught to say prayers at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh yes, we always said our prayers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you ever have family prayers all together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh sometimes we'd - mother would read the bible to us. I had a very large one. And - I had it}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2183526\charrsid6895608  after they died and - and a nie}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 ce of mine came from Buckingham - shire, quite a young girl, she was 
very keen on - all sorts of things. She saw that Bible and she had a look - so she - I said, would you like it? And I gave it to her. I thought it was rather nice. So she's got the family Bible. We had a family Bible, those big ones.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you have a Sunday school outing, a treat or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 I don't think they did in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 You don't remember going anywhere?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 For sports or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No. No. They didn't have Sunday - not like they do now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did your mother attend church and your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh - when we all grew up and that she used to go. And she belonged to the - Bible class at St Marys I think. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 When you were still at home was she too busy on Sunday morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh yes, she had to - all the different children, she hadn't - yes, she couldn't go to church a lot 'til they got - big enough.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did your father go or was he not a churchgoer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 He wouldn't go alone. He wasn't - men went - weren't great churchgoers. Not in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 When you went down to St Botolphs church did you just go on your own with the other children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh yes, with the brothers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 You didn't go with a grown up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No. We used to go on our own you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Can you remember when you were a child if your father had any political views?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh I think he was always Conservative. Always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Do you know why he was Conservative?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Well I think he was mixed up with it with maybe the business men, you see, businessmen, they mix together don't they.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 How was he mixed up with the businessmen, do you mean in his work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Well I think socially they talk you know different - oh he was a - quite a Conservative.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did he belong to any clubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No. I don't think he did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Was your mother also Conservative or was she Liberal or did she not have any views?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh mother was a Conservative with us, we all had the same views. Talk it over on different things, they always did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Would you say they were interested in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh I think they were. Certain amount.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Do you remember your father going to vote before the end of the first war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No I can't remember - but they did vote.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Do you remember what your mother thought about women having the vote and that kind of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh I think she was - quite educated for it the same - she voted. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
At that time a lot of men felt that they had got to vote the way their employers wanted them to, it's particularly true in the country I think, do you know if your father ever felt that he was under pressure?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No, I don't - I never heard him. No. I think he had his ideas - I don't think they interfered with him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Do you know if he was a member of the Conservative party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 I couldn't say in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 And you wouldn't know about your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Do you remember him working for the party, helping the party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No, I don't think he had much time. He was - mind was more with his work and his garden.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 He didn't put up posters or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh I 
think he did. Oh yes. I remember - remember one incident - when I was away - the next door people were great Liberals. And my brothers, they got up one night and they - they - painted }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2183526\charrsid6895608 on }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 the walls the Conservative - yes, on their wall. Oh they were all Conservatives round my side.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Was your husband too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes. I've been always Conservative.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Were you active in politics when you grew up and got }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15757198 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh I - oh yes, I think I am. I think I am now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 And your husband would vote too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh yes, we were both Conservative. In fact I can't stand - the Labour party at all, I can't listen to them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 What about the Liberal party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Well they're - they're fair but I can't understand their principles. I can't under - I've never heard 'e
m saying right out what their principles are.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 It's difficult to know where they stand really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 You don't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Your mother went to this Bible class when she was older?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes, she belonged to a Bible class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Were there any activities outside the home that she did or was she mostly at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
Well she - of course when she had the babies she couldn't do much. It was after the babies got bigger and that that she joined the Bible class. I was away then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did she ever have a friend in for a chat or a cup of tea or go and see them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh I think so, I think she was neighbourly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did they have people for meals in those days, did they entertain to tea or supper?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Not a great deal. Not in our station.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 If somebody came round?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
Oh, they'd have - perhaps - might have a glass of beer or a biscuit or something but - only relations called and had - not outsiders very much. Relations. I think they were more united the relations than they are today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did your mother see a lot of her neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh - just ordinary.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Were they in and out of each other's houses much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No. No. Not a great deal. Not in Gray Road they weren't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 When you were still at school could you play with anyone you liked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 When we went to the playground, yes. We were mixed, girls and boys.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 And all classes at that school were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
Yes. There were - I suppose they went from - a certain age to when they finished school, when they left about fifteen I think se - could leave at fifteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 What sort of families were they round Gray Road, were they mostly your station?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Well they were very select people all round there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 There weren't rough families round there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 All the - no, there was only - two - three children 
next door and one was away and the father and mother, they was - well looking after somebody in Lexden Road, like housekeepers for them. And they had an aunt, these children living next door. I used - I was very friendly with them. And - the aunt had a - 
m
uch to do with the children you see to bring 'em up. But the other side, there was an old lady. Yes. She was a very religious woman. She had one maid living with her. And she was very fussy. And we had to mind our p's and q's with her. Of course my brothe
rs used to play up sometimes. They would do. Annoy her, in little things. And then mother had the - tell them of - anyway we fell in - it kept all right 'til we -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Do you ever remember your mother or father telling you there were certain children you shouldn't play with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 That never arose?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No. No. There was no distinction with children. If they were poor - I think the poor kept away from the others you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 You didn't see very poor round where you lived?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No. Not very. Ther
e might have been a few down the - hospital Road there, these cottages where they're all - still the same. But - we didn't know much of them. We only just went to school and just - and back home and then we mixed with just a few near us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 When you were
 a young girl what were the different classes at that time that you saw, could you describe them to me, the different social classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Well, you see, I went away when I was sixteen. And of course then I left behind everybody and - I didn't mix in my y
ounger days with a lot - only the next door people more or less, we were friends like. Well when I went away then everything changed. You see - I was trained to be a nurse and I loved it. My aunt - it's those two photos were - and - I liked it and I thoug
ht I'd be a nurse. So I - so I did that. And after that well life was different because I was with the gentry all the time. Proper people. Nice people. Very nice people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 What did you think of the gentry, had you met gentry before you went as a nurse?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
No. But they're very homely and very glad to have you. The majority in those days - said they couldn't do without a help. And they - they treated you properly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 They treated you well did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh yes, I never had any - any bother. No, we had
 our rule and regulations. Have a breakfast in the morning - brought up. And - a good breakfast, eggs and bacon and fish and all that. Kedgerll and all that sort of stuff. Proper breakfast. Plenty of milk. Then if we were - just - tidy, had the place tidi
ed up and - off we went out about ten o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 With the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2584098\charrsid6895608 pram}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 I did. You see. Out with the children. Independent, when we were ready off we went. And in the parks and in - \{ILLEGIBLE\}
 Gardens I used to walk through. Round and round there and meet - people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you meet other people?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
Yes. Similar. And have chats and walks and the children used to run about 'til - dinnertime and then we used to go in about twelve and - have an hour - they - have a rest before their dinner. And then their
 dinner came up and - whatever it was, just the same as we have today really, and - then after dinner we went out again 'til about four. Came }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14418699\charrsid6895608 in}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608  and had our tea, and then they played about. They had the games and different things. And then after tea they h
ad to - change all their clothes, everything, put on fresh clothes and go down in the drawing room with their mother and father. For about an hour. And then up they'd come and the mothers come up with them and - and just - sometimes they see 'em into bed,
 they just had a wash before they went to bed. And that was the end of their day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did their mothers see them in to bed or did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 I did - generally. Sometimes she'd come up. They'd come up and have a look.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you bath them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh yes. I bathed - in the morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 When they went downstairs did you go down with them or did they go down on their own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Sometimes they went - if they were small they went - I went with them and just put them in - and then the mothers would sheel them up
. But if they were big enough - they'd - come up theirselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 When you first went it was the Troutbeck family was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes. He was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Was that where your aunt was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No that aunt was - when I went eventually - after being under nurse, I g
ot on my own and and aunt was three of four doors from me. I used to see her. And - I got trained so I knew what to do without much help. And - this aunt - was ill, she died very suddenly so I lost her. Then - I was all right and I carried on 'til the chi
l
dren got - I forget what age it was - the youngest girl, when she got certain age they - they had a French nurse then. When she got a certain age they didn't want a nurse for her. 'Cos the boys were - be - school - Westminster school, they went there the 
two boys.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Were they boarders there or did they go dialu?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes. Daily. Daily. And then they came home at night. 'Cos that only just across the road.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 When you first went there was the girl a baby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 About two years. Yes. Well then when she
 got about - six - like that you see she begun to get too big for a nurse and then they had a governess. They had a French governess take my place.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you meet the governess?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Well the governess used to come in daily before. And then they had th
e governess altogether, as a - then I got the next place to - see - Lawrence, was it. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Was that the M.P. from Melton Mowbray?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes. The M.P. for Melton Mowbray, I forget his name now. Yes. Yes, I went to them and they had -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 What children did they have? The three in the photograph there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
Yes. Yes. They were just those - three children. A boy and two girls. And I went when that was - little girl was about three I think. And - she - Lady Lawrence was it. This child. I think it was. Sir 
Charles - Sir Charles and Lady Lawrence, that's right. They were very nice people. Of course I traveled with them a good bit. Went to Scotland there. Yes, that place. Yes. We - we - stayed in a house belonging to the Duke of Sutherlands, on his estate. An
d
 - oh - that was Fair House, only that he - the big house, they had two houses. We had the small house and - the Sutherlands were a little further on. It was marvellous there - Scotland. Lovely country. I was always hungry. Oh. It was on a hill. Yes, we s
tayed there in the summermonths.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 When you were there on holiday was your routine just the same, did you still have your own quarters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes. We had our own - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 What did the children do there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh - play about. Play about the grounds an
d - more or less. And then while we were there they had - I believe a German governess staying. And she helped, you know, with the children, played games and - I had a photo of her where she was playing that - you know, that Gun Law. Yes. Out in the - out
 in the garden like - she's got her hands up like this playing that thing. And one of the - I haven't got that photo that I - I don't know where it's gone.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 What was she like?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh very good. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 She spoke good English did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 German. 
Yes. Oh they all want to learn English. You see, the French people want to - when they came they want to learn English. I pretty well taught them English. Then the German one was a - the same. So I stayed with - the Lawrences until I }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15757198 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 . And that's where I met my husband there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 When you first went to the Trutbecks Did you have a nursemaid under you to help you or were you just on your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh I had a help. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 What did you call those helps then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Well they - we called them their names you know, just -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 What was her sort of title, was she a nurserymaid, what did they call them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
I think there I had one between for a time. 'Cos there wasn't - that wasn't such a big house. And - yes, that helped with the - the housemaids 'cos -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 And helped you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
Yes. See, there - there were two housemaids there and there were plenty of rooms and they had a lot of work so - they had under housemaid then she came along and helped me - there. She'd bring the breakfast up and do the ro
om and - then you see I was out and - and that. It wasn't hard there. Troutbeck. Oh they were very nice people. 'Cos - he was Coroner for Westminster. And the father was the Presenter in the Abbey and he's buried there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 How much did she have to do with her children besides that hour when they went down to the drawing room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Nothing at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 You brought them up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes. They - they leave you entirely with the children. They only have them down certain times. Just a - you know, just a - if - 
they want them they'll come up in the nursery and talk with them. But they're generally - they were generally out and about doing something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did it seem at all strange to you that they didn't spend more time with them?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No. I was quite happy, I had got me own - I used to do quite a lot of sewing in that time. We used to make a lot of things you know.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you sew the childrens' clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 I used to sew different things and knit and that. Make - make a - certain amount of things you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you ever have any difficulty with the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
Oh yes, you had to - the boys sometimes had - had a pillow fight. When they went to bed they - these two boys - I often thing they were better than what the boys are today. Oh yes. I only want 
to go down the bedroom to tell them be quite, theyr father'd come up to 'em, they - they - they minded. Very obedient.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did the parents ever take the boys out in the evening anywhere with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 I think - yes, the boys used to go out with their parents occasionally. But not very often. Not while they were at school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 How do you think the children felt about their parents when they saw so little of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 I think they though ordinary but they - they enjoyed your co-pany as much as anybody. 
Yes. They're so used to you they call on you in preference to their parents.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 If they had a worry they'd ask you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes. Yes. I remember one - one day - on of the - the little girl I had, she went down to her mothers and she wasn't very good temper
ed and the mother - called me to fetch her up. She couldn't manage her. See, the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Do you think that the mothers ever regretted at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No, I don't think - they - they were so - always doing something, I think that they - just went their way and
 knew the children were all right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Because they knew the children were in good hands?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh yes. Of course they could always run up any time they liked. You see -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did they much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Not a great deal, they often run up and see if you're all right and - have a little chat.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 But you were always upstairs, was it at the top of the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes, the level, it was the level, it was only about three storey hight those places.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Things like table manners and ideas on how to behave, did they get all that from you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes. Only from me, they were just ordinary like they are today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 You were like a mother to them really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes, I was trained well at home and - my aunts too you see, they trained me enough - well manners come and I - 
I have the same manners today as I had then. Don't alter.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 What about things like going to church, did the children go to church on Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No, they didn't go. You see, the mothers sometimes had them. I used to have a Sunday morning off an
d - and one Sunday and evening off the next. And the mothers look after 'em then. They put 'em to bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did the mothers find that difficult do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No, they - they were all right. And - if I - like afternoon I wanted to go out anywhere, I o
nly want to just ask 'em if I can go shopping or anything on my own, they'd - they'd look after the children. Take 'em out just the same. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you ever have a holiday, going away, back home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh yes, I had a holiday, we all - they always gave you holidays. Yes, I used to go home for about a fortnight.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 When you came back did the children seem any different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No, they seem all right, seemed pleased to see you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did they get another person in to help them while you were away?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
Yes. They had a temporary person. Well they had to you see because they didn't - they - they always were doing something, I don't know what it -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 What were they doing, do you know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Well out and about somewhere?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did they go visiting and that type of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
They had - they had parties. Oh yes. And the dresses, they used to dress lovely, Then they - sometimes they'd come up before dinner hour and - show their - they used to dress lovely. I don't think they do now. It's so changed, ever
ything's changed. It was a time of grandeur in those days. Dinner parties and - a lot of - meetings with people and that - lots of parties.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you ever meet any of the people that came to the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh sometimes they'd come up in the nursery. A
nd see the children. Homely. And when they had - I don't know whether they - what sort of people they were, they - of course they had clubs and different things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 What did you think about the gentry and their way of life at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 I thought t
hey were very good. To - to what - the life I had I've no complaints. They weren't stuck up, they were genuine, much better than people today that - the Jones's, I don't like those sort of people. Jumped up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 What were their manners like?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 I - I l
ike educated people to talk to and I - I like to listen to them. But I don't like these that know all. I hate those sort of people. 'Cos everybody's brought up natural, you can't help being poor and they're natural, I don't mind them. But I hate these peo
ple - snobs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you think the gentry were snobbish?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No. They're very natural. They're - they're brought up - to respect you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you ever have a dispute with anybody about how the children were brought up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 It never came up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
No. They were always satisfied, there was - no disputes or - nothing - and I remember once we'd had a lot of eggs for tea and the children got tired of them. And I'd just had to say, would you mind them not having eggs for a bit, they've got tired of 
them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Who did you say that to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 The lady. And she gave the orders you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 You didn't give orders to the cook?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No. Never. No, they - they don't like you doing that. The - the kitchen people are really jealous of - nurses a little bit.
 You don't go down very much. Not to-
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you mix with them sometimes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
Well some times of the year, lady - the lady's maid'd come in and have a chat and so would the housemaid, but I hardly ever saw the cooks. Hardly ever. They - they - that was a different group altogether.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you ever find that there or at Melton Mowbray they were quarrelling among themselves ever?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No. The - no, they were very happy family. The families I lived with were very happy and seemed to be well organized.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 What about the cook and the other people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh well they all -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did they ever quarrel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
No. The - the people I was with were always nice to me and I never had any complaints. The food was good and there was never - nothing said - up horrible. All good and clean.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you ever go into the kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh yes, I did occasionally but - hardly - hardly ever, only about - say once a month I might go down and speak to them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Otherwise you kept up in your own quarters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes. I came 
in and - and - went to me rooms and - and all that sort of thing and - had - didn't do - have much to do with - you come in contact with the housemaid and we used to go and stay away sometimes to the country houses, and have nice times in the gardens and 
that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did the children ever question the way that they weren't brought up by their mothers but by you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
No, no, natural - they didn't - took it - yes. I think if you - if - they got a bad nurse and a grumbly old woman and - you know, somebody that didn't studay them. They wouldn't - they'd kick up bad, the children would.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 But they were happy with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Well I - I never had any complaints. It is - makes you - if you're naturally fond of children and - been used to 'em I think you know how
 to manage 'em. Even now I can manage children. I mean - often speak to little children and - they smile at me, you know, I love to see them. Fond of children now. Seemed funny I had none.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did they ever have friends to play, did they ever play with other children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
Not often. Only in their - when they were - they'd run about with the children out in the gardens. When you were out - taking them out they'd mix with other children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 But other children didn't come to tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Well, only - only relations that - relations would come but - they didn't have a lot of parties, not really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you ever take them to a house for afternoon tea or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No. No. We went to parties. If there was a birthday party we'd go to the - tea parties.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 It would be you, not the mother, who took them to parties?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes, I'd - I'd stay with 'em you see, all the time. Come back with them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Who shopped for their clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh the mothers. The mothers bought their clothes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you go along too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No. They always brought in what they want - for the children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you tell the mother if things were needed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No, I think they - well, if they - anything worn out I'd tell 'em. And - if they - they'd have shoes and that all sent up to t
ry on and choose.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 After you left the Troutbecks did you ever see those children again?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh yes. 'Cos after - I mean - after I left and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15757198 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608  I had this appe dicitis bad. And I had to go to Leicester Infirmary - Leicester hospital. And after I came out there she came - the this is - Lady }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12864430\charrsid6895608 Troutbeck}
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608  and she fetche me and took me to her house and I stayed there a fortnight. Yes, and I - she - brought }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12864430\charrsid6895608 m}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 e every day. Come up and saw me in bed and everything.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Was that in London or was it a house in the country she took you too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 That - no, it was a - down in Melton Mowbray, when they were there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 That was Lady Troutbeck?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes. No, that was Lady Lawrence. The last place.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 After you left the Troutbecks, did you ever see their children again?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No. I never saw -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you know how much your husband earned when you were first }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15757198 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Well I don't think we got about three pound a week then. And the house. That was the usual.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 How did you budget the money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Well, t
hings was cheap. I mean - eggs. You'd get - twenty-four for a shilling in those days. Bacon you'd get - bacon, eighteenpence a pound of good bacon. Bread was about tuppence a loaf. Butter was about a - shilling a pound.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did he give you all the money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No. I had about - thirty shillings, so about half of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 What did the rest go to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Well we saved for different things and - outings, we had a holiday you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 You had savings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Where did you save, in a bank?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Well we - if I had - and I - I had some money when I was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15757198 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608  that my hubby never touched. My savings - he never touched it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 That was your own money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes, and that all was my money, he wouldn't touch a penny of mine.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 How did you manage to save that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Well - when I was in service I saved it - a few pound you know and I kept putting in in the - Post Office.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Had he got any savings when you were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15757198 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes, he was pretty well off. Well - moderately, he was careful - we were caref
ul. Not like today with all that - this - we were fond of cycling, we both had a cycle.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Where did you go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 We used to go to farm houses, people that have got farmhouses and have a cup of tea. Nice cream for tea and all that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 When would you go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 In the evenings, in summer evenings off we used to go and stay - and see these people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you ever go off for a weekend cycling or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No. We always - my hubby always came back at night while we - until we had our holiday you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you go away for a holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes. We used to come to Colchester, come home here. And see my parents.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 And stay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes. Fortnights holiday. He used to go to Somerset tool. He had - relations at Taunton, we went there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 He was born in Somerset wasn't he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes. Taunton.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you go and stay there too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
Yes, we stayed there with relations and they were hairdressers I remember. And we'd have a fortnight there sometimes and then - when we had another fortnight we came to Colchester, see my people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 So you went away every year did you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh yes, always had a fortnight every year somewhere.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you make any clothes or did you buy them all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 I used to make some - some of the things. B
ut - the stuff - the clothes were cheap. You could get a pair of shoes for six shillings, as - quite as good as what you pay four pounds today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 You bought shoes readymade did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 How were the shoes mended?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Well - there were men - you could take them to, would heel and mend - dod that sort of work you see. Like there are today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did your husband ever mend them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No. He was no good, he was a gardener. He was no good for anything but the gardening and - and looking after
 the glasshouses you see. He had - always be on duty unless one of the men - if we went away one of the men'd come and - see to the greenhouses. 'Cos he grew - all sorts of things, peaches and grapes and - flowers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 How many evenings a week would your husband be at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
Oh we - we wouldn't go out perhaps only for the weekends. Sometimes on a Saturday we - might not go out - all the week because, with gardeners, they have got a lot to do. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 What time would he finish in the summer evenings in the week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Well - you see, summer evenings you had to go late in the greenhouses and - shut them up. And water them. So - a gardener's tied.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 What time would he go and shut them up then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Well - I - I think he used to go between seven and
 eight. About that. According to the season, see. If it was - hot summer he'd shut them up later. If it was wintertime - close 'em quite early.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did he ever like to go for a drink at the pub?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No. He didn't - he didn't drink. No, he was a - quiet 
- in the choir you see. Church choir. And then he just had the - rehearsals and - and then we were both were in Sir Malcolm Sargeants choir. So we had -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you go to choir practices?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes, we had to go to them. Yes. Otherwise we must garden you see. Had a big garden.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you get to know any other people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
Oh yes. Several people. Oh yes. And - they - the - see the - schoolmaster there, of the village, there was a village, he got up a - sort of mission hall and we used to go to that. And
 then, one Sunday - did I tell you that before? I played the organ once. Yes. Well - the organist didn't turn up and I played it like a piano. I didn't know how to do it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 What did it sound like?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 All right. Yes. And - it passed off all right. And
 then we used to give a - in this hall, they had a - party once a year and then - we took - I used to supply all the cakes and things for so many, just like they're doing now today. They give all the people that came - evening. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you ever have a lodger while you were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
No. There was nothing of those - that sort. Not in our days. No, I don't think there was much of lodgers. I never had a lodger 'til I was here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you ever have a relation living with you there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No. Stay - they used to come and stay. Oh yes. Visitors.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Was that nice?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes. Oh yes, my sisters used to come and - stay for a week or two you see, from school, they used to - when they were at school holidays.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Because they were so much younger?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 How did you do your washing then, did you do it at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
Just ordinary washing like we do now, only we didn't have the soap powders then you know, we had - soap and a little soda I think in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you do it like your mother had done hers, the same way?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes. Boil anything that - you could or - and generally had coppers then, I've got a copper here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 When you were a nurse how did the childrens' clothes get washed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh they were - the laundry. Every week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 You didn't wash anything for them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Nothing. No. Always a laundry who got it ready and they were fetched every week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Was the same true of your clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 All together, yes, and come back together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 When you were a nurse you didn't wear uniform?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No, I didn't. Some did but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Was that unusual?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
Well, no, some ladies didn't bother. If they wore uniform - they generally bought them. Whereas I bought my own clothes. But I used to wear a lot of grey. Grey costumes - and hat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 When you were a nurse did you mend the childrens' clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh yes. If they had odd - odd things. Not a lot, there wasn't a lot of mending needed. Not in children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you mend clothes when you were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15757198 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh yes. Oh yes. I - if there was anything, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Where did you buy clothes when you were in Melton Mowbray, what sort of a shop, was there a shop there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh yes, they were clothiers, just similar, I forget about the clothes but I used to buy my clothes when I needed them. Just - ordinary.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Not at special occasions or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 I had enough clothes 'cos I - I made a lot of my -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you have a trousseau?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes. I made all my clothes, hand did. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you and your husband discuss money and how you should spend it or didn't you need to discus it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
Oh yes. If there was anything we wanted we discussed it. And otherwise - if I wanted any I just said to him, I'd like a little more, can I have it? He'd - he left it to me to go and get it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Three pounds was quite a good wage then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh yes. Quite a good wage. 'Cos we had no house rent or anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 A lot of people were getting a pound a week or even less then weren't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did your husband ever do any cooking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No. He was no cook. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 What about cleaning or washing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did he - was he responsible for repairing the house or did the landlord do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Well there was very little done while I was there. It was fairly good condition.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did your husband make the fires or did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh I did. I generally lit the fires.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Was there anything he did in the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No. No, he didn't do any. He was - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did your own father do things in the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No. He was another - no, he didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 He was with his allotment?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes. He had the allotment.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Where did you eat your meals in that house in Melton Mowbray?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh we had the dining room like we do here. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 What did you have to cook on then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Ordinary oven. Coal fire with oven. An
d a - hot water - little system this side - which we put the water in there daily, see, and I - I had it hot that side, nice oven there. Mind you, used to cook better in that - those stoves than they do today in ovens. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 You like that to cook on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh yes. Well them gas came in after - during the time I was away and I had a gas stove then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you always eat in the dining room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 You didn't eat sometimes in the kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No, I had rather a small kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you have a best room too or a parlour or a front room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh yes, we had a - front sitting room. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 But you didn't eat there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No. We used to sit there and - in the evenings if we wanted. Light a fire you see, fires in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you have a cooked breakfast in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes. I always had - ever since I can remember. Oh yes. I - I eat very little at night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Was your main meal in Melton Mowbray midday dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes. Midday dinner. Similar to what I have now. 'Cos we had 
the vegetables, the different vegetables and all - meat was cheaper. And better.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you have meat - how often would you have meat then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Meat? Oh I had meat every - every day. Yes. And fish.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 These are questions that don't apply to you because you were comfortable weren't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes. Yes. They don't - I - I never wanted. No. No. All those things. I never wanted.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 You didn't have any hens or pigs or goats?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 What about for tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Well tea similar to what - if we felt 
we want an egg or ham or anything for tea we had it. Just as - just as we felt. And I used to make cakes and that. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you have anything different for tea on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No, I don't think we made much difference.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you have a joint on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh yes. Always had a joint. I still have it. Yes. Not too big now though.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you have a piano in the house at Melton Mowbray?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes. Oh yes, I had a piano.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did your husband play too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No, he - he was a good singer, I used to play it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you ever have a musical evening there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Occasionally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 With friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes, occasionally, we had the different people come in and - had a sing-song. Like we did at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 You said how lovely it was at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh yes. Oh yes, my hubby was very fond of music and so was I you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Were there any other musical instruments?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Well there was nothing much in the village like, not really because -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you have anything else in your home, like a violin or was it just the piano?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
Oh my husband had a concertina. In his young days, yes, he used to play it - but that didn't go with a piano though. He didn't get - he didn't do much with it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you ever play just for him to sing, just the two of you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Well I used to help him with his tenor.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 With his parts you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4792909\charrsid6895608 P}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
art singing and church, if he'd got Anthem and they wanted to practice and I - I'd pick out his tenor notes and help him with it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 What about Christmas, what did you do at Christmas when you were in Melton Mowbray.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh well we had - we used to have a plum pudding and a cake and - just - just ordinary does but I can't remember much about Christmases.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did anyone come and visit or did you go and visit do you remember at Christmas?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 I forget about Christmas. It don't stand out. Not too much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you have any books, was your husband a reader?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh - yes, we got lots of books and - lots of gardening books I had and I gave them all away 'cos I don't 
want them, I was lumbered with books.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 He read a lot about gardening dod he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh he - he had all the - whole heap of books.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 It was his real passion in life was it, his gardening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh well, that was his life, gardening you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 That was his bobby and his work and everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 I think so. I think he was - well, he was well up in it and he studied it, he didn't worry about - not latterly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did he get any magazines about gardens?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Magazines? I think he used to take a garde
ner, yes, he used to take gardening - for any extra. And of course he belonged to the garden society. Yes. He did in Colchester too. 'Cos he used to go - places - well - with - jusdging you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 That was how you met him of course?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes. Yes. Judging. Even in Colchester did it - did some judging around here. When we were here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you have a daily paper then or can't you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh yes, we always had daily paper.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 What did you get in Melton Mowbray?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 I - I think it was something of the concern now - I think it's similar. I don't know, can't remember what but we always had -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Was it the Daily Mail?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 I think it must have been.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you belong to a library?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No, I didn't, I - I didn't read so much there. Not the library. Did you see about Colchester library.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Do you remember going out on a Bank Holiday at Melton Mowbray?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Going out to holidays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 On a Bank Holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No, we didn't go out Bank Holidays because there were too many people about. You s
ee they - nearly all the poorer people in my young days, they used to go out Bank Holidays to the sea or somewhere and - we didn't go on those days because that was too crowded.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 When you were a young }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15757198 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608  woman did you think it was wrong to work on a Sunday or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
Yes. I - I - I still don't like too much work on a Sunday. I feel - that God has given us that day of rest and we should respect it and keep it. I always and my husband has said, rather than I cook on the Sunday he'd go without and 
have a piece of bread and cheese. We never - never cooked.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 You never cooked on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No. Cooked on the Saturday always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 When did you have your joint then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Saturday. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 I thought you said on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No. We had - alway
s had - I do now. And then I go to church Sunday and I have a cold dinner - Sundays and I generally warm something what I've got. Egg custard generally on Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 And you used to do that too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh we used to have different puddings. I used - could eat more then you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did your husband like puddings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh yes. Cakes and puddings, he was fond of puddings. I made - all sorts of puddings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 He was also Church of England?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh yes, of course that was church you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 You had this mission hall there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Were there any other clubs or organizations there you took part in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
Well - I don't think there was very much of it 'cos it was a group - just a small place where there big houses all round, gentry, and a lot of peo
ple worked and helped these places that I - don't think there were much in the evenings to entertain them. Not then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 You never went to a cinema there or a play or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No. No, I - there wasn't any. Not in my time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 When it was just you and your husband did you say grace or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh no, we didn't say grace.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 That was for children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Children. Oh no, we used to often say, thank God for this, like you would.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 But not grace?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No. No grace as - not in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you read the Bible at all then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Occasionally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 I'm interested to know the part religion played in peoples lives you know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh yes. I think they were more religious, my husband is a - well he was - I've got his ol
d Bible here and I remember I picked it up there's different parts he used to study. In his young days he must have been quite a good living man. People used to read their Bibles in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Was there a chapel in Melton Mowbray, a non-conformist church or chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Not that I know of. I never heard of one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Everyone was Church of England there were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes, I think it's all - might have been a small place but - I never heard of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Were there any sort of rough people there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
No they all seemed ordinary homely people. I don't think there were the poverty there that there are in the towns you know. 'Cos that's a village and they all find work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 There didn't seem to be rough families there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No. No. I didn't see no - didn't notice - not really hard up people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 The schoolmaster you knew, who did he have his social life with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Well - he started this - mission and he got different people to help him, you see my hubby helped and I helped. And we used to get nice ev
enings and of course he was an educated man and carried it out very well.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
Did he associate with the gentry, did they entertain him in their homes and that type of thing or how did the schoolmaster fit into the social life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Well - well, I - I - 
of course the - gentry don't - didn't come - come to church, they - not to the mission hall. They'd go to church. They'd probably go to church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 I wondered if a schoolmaster would be entertained by the gentry, would he go to dinner parties there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No. I don't think so. Not in that - 'cos I think they kept themselves more in that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Was there a local doctor?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes, and he was a very homely man, very friendly with us. And especially after I had my operation he used to come down a
nd walk round the garden and - loved the garden you know. And he used to tell me what to do and not to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Took an interest in you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes. He did. A very nice man, he was a very homely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did the doctor mix with the gentry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 I don't know. 
Well I suppose they did if they were anything wrong. Unless they had their special - special people from London. 'Cos you see, in those days - there was more distinction wasn't there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 How far away was Craven Lodge from the house of the Yates family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 They were - in - the village. Well - a couple of miles. Yes. Ashby.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you ever see them, she took you to convalesce didn't she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes. Yes. Yes. Well of course I was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15757198 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608  then. And - but then afterwards you see they'd go back to London f
or the season and then I didn't see much of them then. Gradually weened off. And then - they were in London, well there was only the ladies maid that would correspond to me and tell me the goings on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 What sorts of things did she tell you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh tel
l you - she told me what the children were doing and - of course they were grown up then and - getting out and about. And then she was left and of course died and - everything went. And I didn't hear any more.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 After you first got }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15757198 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
 did you ever see the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh yes. Oh yes, I saw them, they -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you go and visit them or did they come and see you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Well I visited them, you see. Generally. 'h yes, they - they were always pleased to see me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Do you remember their names?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 The boys was Charles. The girl -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 There were two girls weren't there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes. Yes, their names have gone. Can't remember. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 You used to save up for things like a holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you save through a club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No. Save at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you have a tine or something?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you ever belong to clubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No. No. No. Never had any - everything to do with putting so much by in anything. Only money if I - put any by in the Post Office.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Didn't you believe in slate clubs and clothing clubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Well I didn't have enough to throw about. To put in clubs I don't think then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Was there any Womens Institute or anything like that there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Not as I know of. No, there wasn't much at that church, not really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you have any pets while you were there, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4792909\charrsid6895608 did you have a cat}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608  or a dog or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No, I didn't have a dog. No, not there. No. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you do any gardening yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 You had no relatives of your own living nearby there did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No, I was right away 'cos they all lived here. You see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Was it Lady Yates?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did she come to see you when you got il}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4792909\charrsid6895608 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608  then and say she'd look after you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh when I was ill? Oh yes, well she didn't come, she had me there to stay with her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did she write to you and offer you the chance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
Oh yes, after I got - went off home and then of course they eventually - soon after that went to London. And they're in London all the winter. And then just go to Ashbury House for - summer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
You say you had rooms when you were a nurse, what did the rooms consist of? In the Troutbeck house, the one in London, what were the rooms that you had?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Well - they were all one - on one - landing. You had your bathroom, just - one side, you
r dining room next and two bedrooms off - off that room. Yes. Well that was all - that was your lot you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Where did the children sleep at the Troutbecks?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh - well they slept - off the - the living room. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 All in the one room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Y
es. I slept - had a bed in the same room with them. And then - where the boys were, they had a room downstairs, lower down, the next landing, the boys.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you sleep with the girl then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes. The girl - just girl in one bed, me in another, in this bedroom.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 And the boys downstairs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes. They had - the next - downstairs, the bedroom there where the two boys slept down there.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Was there another bedroom in your set of rooms? Was that for playing or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Well this was the playing and dining - and dining room all in one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 That's where you had your meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes. Dining room, play - all together. Fairly big room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did they call it a nursery in those days or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 They called it a nursery?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes. The nursery, always, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did they ever have any meals with their own parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Only a tea sometimes. Not - not often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Not dinner or midday dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No. No, they didn't have - go down - not much, even the boys didn't, not at that time. No,
 they were - had their own friends in with them but they didn't have the children. Not in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 When you got there did you find that the manners that they had at table were as you liked or did you have to change things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh - could change things if you liked them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you want to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No. We had a nice bedroom and - just the - similar to what of course they - in those days everybody had good stuff.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did they behave at table like you wanted them to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Or did you have to get them to your ways?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes they were natural. You see - their natural ways were mine.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 It was the same?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes. There was no trouble with them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Was it the same with the Yates's?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes, they're all about the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 The manners were the same?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
Oh yes. They don't - you don't often - with those children have to tell them much. They're sort of born to it. Yes, the manners were similar to what they are today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did they say grace?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did they say prayers at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you teach them or did they already know that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
They - they were - well - they already had their prayers and the mother used to often come and hear them. Oh yes, she always used to come up and say goodnight to the children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 That was both those mothers was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
Yes. Oh mostly come and say goodnight. If they were at home. And if they were they'd hear their prayers. Oh yes, they were brought up to - to prayers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did they learn the piano or anything like that, the Troutbeck children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
Not my - not while I was there. 'Cos they - they - well - the boys were at school you see, and the girl, she - she just got about - just that age to begin. And then I left 'cos they had a governess.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Were the Yates children learning any musical instruments?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No. They didn't have any musical - it was more outdoor life you know all the time. You see - they don't - have only just their morning -

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Was there anything about the London job that you particularly liked or disliked?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
I was happy there. Yes. And I used to have Sunday morning off to church. And I used to go to St Margarets church and there was a lovely choir there and - I used to enjoy it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 St Margarets, Westminster?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes. Yes. Yes, I used to go there Sunday mornings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 When you went out in the evenings was it once a week or once every second week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Well - if I didn't want to go I didn't ask for the - to go. I used to go as I felt.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Could you go more than once a week if you wanted to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No, I don't think so, I think you were allowed - that was the allowance.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Once a week in the evening or was it every other week you were allowed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Once a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 If you did go out where would you go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Well - I had a friend I used to go and visit. Otherwise I hadn't got - much - to do with it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 You didn't have a young man while you were in London?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you have to be in by a certain time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Well - I never stayed out late, I didn't want to be late. I think they allowed you out 'til - ten probably.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 But you don't remember this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No, I never stayed out after nine, I was mostly home about nine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Was it Mrs Troutbeck, not Lady Troutbeck?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Mrs Troutbeck.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did she ever talk to you about how you should behave or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Or how it could be dangerous for a young girl in London?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
No, she never. No. She - no. Well I didn't go - you see - I wasn't one to - to be walking about the streets. And - I preferred to be in on the dark nights, I didn't go out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did she sometimes come up and sit and talk in the nursery?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh yes, she'd come and talk, or sit down and chat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 What sort of things would she talk about?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Well everyday things or the children you see. Everyday things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did she ever play with the children herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh yes, often played with them. Used to come up and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Were they at ease with her do you think or do you think they felt a little strange with her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No, they - were free with their mothers. Oh ye
s, there was no - if they didn't like anything they wouldn't do it with their mothers. Really. Yes. Oh they were - they were brought up quite homely with their mothers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 What about their fathers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Well they didn't see so much of their fathers 'cos mainly they were out and about doing work - something or other.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did the children at the Troutbecks or the Yates's have any jobs they had to do to help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 They didn't do anything to help like you had done as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No. No. No, the
y were free just to amuse theirselves and play. And - in fact I often used to teach them things you see. The young ones I taught them - lessons in the first beginning. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 What did you teach them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 I taught them - all the letters and spelling an
d I - I begun the first lot - lot of teaching with them. Yes. Amuse them - they like it you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 So they knew something when the governess came?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh yes. They knew - they could read a little bit and that. Oh yes, I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did the boys have a governess too at first?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No, they were at school. The boys were at school when I was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Day boys or boarders?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Day boys, day boys.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 It was so nearby wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes. It's a lovely school, Westminster.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did they go to boarding school afterwards so you know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 I think they did after I left. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 That bathroom you had, were the children always bathed up there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Was that every day or once a week or how often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 When you felt like it - really. I - I don't think
 - we didn't have them every night. Not in those days. Just as you felt the - need of the bath you gave them a bath.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 What time did you put the Troutbeck children to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Well now the boys went to bed about - just after eight and the little girl went about - seven. Never late.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 What about the cooking, did you know about that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
No. No. I didn't come in any contact with the cooking. The lady gave the orders for what - daily and - we didn't know what we - we were going to have.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Mrs. Troutbeck didn't have a housekeeper did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did Lady Yates have a housekeeper?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No. No. They didn't have housekeepers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 They supervised themselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 They supervised all that on their own. Yes. Used to go down and give their orders every morning. For the day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 So you wouldn't know things like if the cook made bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Or jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 I - I - don't think they made bread, not in my time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Do you know what kind of cooker they had in the kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh big - big - ovens like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Coke and coal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes. In those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Do you know if the parents had the same food as the children and you or did they have different food?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 I couldn't say. We lived just like ordinary people, the children had meat and potatoes and - just the ordinary.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did the parents eat in the dining room downstairs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 They had theirs in the dining room, a big dining room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Was it just the two of them, the Troutbecks, or were there any older grown up children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No, the children were at school you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 There weren't any older grown up children or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Well - on holidays - the - the boys'd might - go down to lunch with their parents. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did they have to be specially neat and tidy then?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh yes, tidy. They dare not go down rough and - hair all about. All washed and brushed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 But the little girl didn't go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No. She - no, she never went.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 That was just holidays they had the midday meal there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes. When we were away holidays and 
that then they were with their parents more the boys. And - when we went away we all used to play cricket sometimes in the gardens. Yes, the boys and - all of us you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Mother and father too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Sometimes. They'd amuse them you know if they - wanted to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Do you remember if the mother ever read to the Troutbeck children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 She might have in the evenings when they went down to - in the evenings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did they talk to you about what they did down there in the drawing room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Sometimes, but not a lot. They took it as just a dressed up affair I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 They didn't like dressing up like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No. They had to change everything, petticoats and - dresses an socks and shoes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Just for a short time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes. Just for half an hour. Only half an hour.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Was it the same on Sunday afternoon, every day of the week would they go down?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
Well if the mothers were in - sometimes they'd come up to the nursery, but they wouldn't go down - not to be down with their parents. Not really. 
See, real - real nobs as you call - the well-to-do people, the moneyed people. But no one'll tell me they were hard on the poor. It's only in towns perhaps where they were jumped up people that got money and they kept the poor down more than the - the rea
l gentry because - the gentry were pleased to have - the help, they couldn't do without us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
You were telling me there was a time when you had to come and fetch the little girl back because she was a bit naughty, were there any other incidents like that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
No, I think - only remember once. And the mother was cross with her. She said, oh no, she said, I brought her up, she - I can't manage her. Leave her to you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 She always called you nurse did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Was that Mrs Troutbeck?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes. And they both called me nurse.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Mrs Yates too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 What did the children call you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Nanny.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 The same at Lady Yates'?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 What did you call them, did you call them Miss and Master or just their names?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh I - I - when you spoke to them you call them my Lady, if you spoke to Lady Lawrence. You'd - you'd say m'lady to her. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 And to Mrs Troutbeck?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Mrs Troutbeck, ma'am. Generally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 What about the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh the children always said mother or father or anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 What did you call the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh by their names.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 If the name was John you wouldn't say Master John?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang1034\langfe1033\langnp1034\insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang1034\langfe1033\langnp1034\insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No. Oh no. No, no. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 It wasn't - no, we didn't call them masters, not nurses didn't. They were - ordinary children to us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 The cook would have called them master would she?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh yes. They would. So would the housemaids.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Everybody but the nurse?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Because you were different weren't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Well - you were training those children, with them all the time and you - just respected their - their parents you see but not the -

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 The children you just treated like children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Do you ever remember having to tell the children how to behave towards their brothers and sisters, were they quarrelsome?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
Well - they - sometimes you - you'd - find they might be a little bit - but - they weren't very bad, I often think how - wonderful those children were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Do you ever remember if they were hit by another child or anything what you told them to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 I didn't have that. No, no, there was nothing of that. No, there was - in those days they didn't fight and quarrel like they do today.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 It seems altogether better for children in some ways?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh I think so. I think there's better times for everybody.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did the mother ever ask how the children were eating?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh yes. Oh yes, she said - always wanted to know if they were all right and they enjoyed their food. Oh yes, the mothers all asked that.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did they ever come up during a meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Not often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you ever have to punish any of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 You never did?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No, they used to do what they were told somehow.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Like you had done as a child, you weren't punished were you when you were a little girl?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No. My father - mother was too good natured.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did your father ever punish you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
No. He'd hit the boys, he had to send them to bed. And he said they had to go to bed and no tea, but mother crept up and took 'em some. She was too easy going, my mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 What sort of a person was your mother really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Well - oh very - very calm and - not at all bad tempered. Very easy going. I think I had a wonderful mother. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Was your father easy going too or was he more strict?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
He was more strict. But he was kind. Oh yes he was strict but kind, he was - he didn't hurt anybody or - but he did - I know he did - hit the boys once but - I remember that once. Well he had to do - do it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Do you remember any of the children you looked after ever swearing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 You really had no trouble at all with them all those years?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 It seems strange now doesn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes. Well the children are different today. Oh - they're born older and they've got more - more
 brain. They're different. We were - had discipline and - we had to mind them, they were - well, natural.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 When you were at the Troutbecks did the children have birthday parties?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes. Occasionally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Where would that be, would that be downstairs or up in the nursery?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Well - yes, they'd have them in the nursery.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did they have a birthday cake and that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh yes, had birthday cakes. And they went out to birthday parties.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Were you at the Troutbecks on Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
No, I - I - we had - I can't remember Christmas. I can't remember Christmases. No, I can't remember them. Well I suppose my life was full and - we had fairly good Christmases. I can't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 You don't know whether you came home or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 I never come home for Christmas. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Was there any funeral in the family at the Troutbecks or the Yates'?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No. No funerals.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did the Troutbecks have a lot of books?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh yes, books to read and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Could you read their books?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh yes, they were childrens books you know. Oh yes, we -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 You didn't read the Troutbeck's books?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh - the Troutbecks had - they always had all the - latest books you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Could you borrow their books if you wanted to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Well I re
ad 'em, they're in the nursery. All the books there you see. We had a cupboard with all their things in. Toys and books and everything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did they have grown up books in the nursery as well as childrens books?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No. They had - only had the childrens' books up there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you read aloud to the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Occasionally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did they like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh yes, I - there's a lot of sayings now when I hear on the telly the books I used to read. Yes.;
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Can you think of any?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Well - seem a long time ago. The - the different sayings but I can - sometimes they co}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2252721\charrsid6895608 me b}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 ack on the tely you see those things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you ever go away for a weekend with the Troutbecks or the Yates'?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh yes, we went away for months with 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you ever go away just for a weekend?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No. No, we used to go away for lengthy - holidays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did they ever go away for a weekend on their own, the Troutbecks?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Well they may have done, I - really I - couldn't say. I think they did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 If they were away over a weekend would you get a message not to send the children down?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
Oh - they went away 'cos I had to write to - we went away as the - the children were away from their mother and I had to write to 'em about their children. Yes. To say how they were and what they were doing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 When they went away for quite a long time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
When they went - yes, when they went away they'd write to us and want to know how the children were. I used to have to write every week while we were away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you ever go away with the children somewhere?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes, alone. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 You didn't go to Frinton I suppose?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 I can't - I can't - forget the place, we - no - no, we never went to Frinton. We were - not - not often -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 You generally went on another estate did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes, we went away - stayed with relations sometimes. Their grandma. And - we stayed away a month sometimes with them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 And then you'd write?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 I write every week. Yes. I remember going to - Lord Chief Justice he was - and - they had all these - matched footmen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 In pairs was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
That was in - in the - un London they had them and in the country, the coaches you see. They had matched - footmen - footmen. And butlers. This house where we went - went to stay was a very big house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 You had your rooms there as well did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes, just the same. And - had our meals served just the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you ever get friendly with the footmen and bu}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2252721\charrsid6895608 t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 lers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh yes, one of - oh yes, they used to tease me a bit sometimes. Yes. O
h yes, we had - they used to joke about us you know. You always get that with men.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you ever sit with them in the evenings and talk and the other maids?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh no. I kept upstairs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you ever get to make any friends with people in the country so that you corresponded afterwards or saw them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
Oh yes, we did, my hubby knew a lot of people. And - we did for a few years, but - and then we went back and stayed there once. Then I lost my little dog. I had a little pom. A little brown one, ab
out four pound, I used to take it everywhere where I went. I used to take it in - on a bacicle in a basket. And we took this dog to Me}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2252721\charrsid6895608 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 ton Mowbray to stay with friends and they had a dog. And we wanted to go out and the friend said, leave - your dog behind
, that'll be all right. But somebody went and opened the door and the dog ran out to find us and got run over. I never had another dog since.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you ever take the children to your home at all at Colchester?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No. No. No, you never brought them do
wn like that. I wouldn't have conveniences for them in the houses. 'Cos they'd have their own places you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Thinking of the Troutbecks, would you say all their friends were the same social class as themselves, the same station?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh yes, I think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 And the same was true of the Yates?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes. Yes, they had their own friends - on an equal - really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Would you say that the Troutbecks' and the Yates' were quite content with their position in life or do you think they hoped to get a bett
er, higher position?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 I think they were happy with their - position, yes. Never heard anything to the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 To the contrary?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 In your house in Gray Road you had four bedrooms?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Can you remind me what other rooms you had?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh I had a front sitting room, a dining room and a kitchen. Bigger than these.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 You had no relatives or lodgers there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 You moved there when you were quite a young child didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Very young, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 But you're not sure of the age?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No, I can't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 About seven do you think, or older than that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 About that I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did your parents live on there until they died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No. The house was sold and - my father wouldn't buy it. He could have bought i
t quite cheap, he wouldn't borrow money and we had to leave. And then mother went - they went up to - Hamilton Road.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Was that after you'd left?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 After I'd - yes, after I'd been away a long time.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you go to Ireland straight after leaving school or were you at home for a while?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 I - let me see, I think I was - almost after I left school I went around about - I must have gone about sixteen I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Straight after leaving school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes, I - yes, I - that was my first place on my own.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 In Ireland?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh no, with aunt. Yes, I was taught there. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 But the very first time you went in nurseries?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 I went holidays. When the under nurse went for holidays you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 While you were still a schoolgirl was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 W
ell - I should think I must have gone after I'd left school. Left school about fifteen you know. And then that's - I used to go up then, 'til I made up me mind to take it up all together you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 You said your mother used to pay somebody to help with the children when she had a confinement?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Where did that friend come from, was she Colchester?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Come from - yes - from Fordham Heath.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 It wasn't the same couple you used to go and visit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 You said your grandfather kept a shoeshop in St Botolphs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes. Yes.;
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Do you remember him at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Very little. I just remember my grandmother - grandfather died first and I just remember my grandmother, only just.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you get your shoes at that shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 I couldn't say. I think we must have done.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did your mother}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2252721\charrsid6895608  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 make clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes, she was a very good at - hand - they didn't have machines in those days I don't think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did she get secondhand clothes sometimes or were they always new?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
Well - she used to make all the clothes when I was young. Well then, when I got away and we had certain clothes that fitted my younger sisters I used to send a lot home. And they weren't bad clothes you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 When your mother did buy clothes do you remember where she bought them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No, I can't remember that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Do you remember her mending?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh yes, she mended. She had to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 She had nobody to help her in the house on normal occasions did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No. She used to do all herself. And we helped you know in between. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 What time did you have to go to bed when you were a small child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
Well we used to have to go to bed quite early. I should say, when I was tiny I went to bed about seven o'clock and as we got older we went eight and - always all of us in before nine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Even when you were about fourteen you'd be in bed by nine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes. We didn't sit up late.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Can you remember being put to bed or don't you remember that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No. I can't remember that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 You bathed by the fire on a Saturday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes. Oh we hadn't bathrooms then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 When did you have clean clothes on, clean underclothes?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Every - Sunday. Clean things every Sunday for church. All clean things on a Sunday clothes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Were the children you looked after the same, did they have clean }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2252721\charrsid6895608 th}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 ings on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes, I think we did. Well they used to have - the children I looked after had - if they were grubby I'd put them on any time you see. Yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 You used to help cleaning the knives and forks?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you do that after you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No, while we went to school we had to do that. On Saturdays. Anything that wants cleaning we had to clean. They were ste}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1449583\charrsid6895608 el knives in those times. Not}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 - like they are today. We had to rub them on a board.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 That must have been very hard work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Well they kept - they cut well. Better than the knives today. Real steel, I've got a few now. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 What were the different social classes in Colchester in the early years before you went away when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Well there's very little.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 What class would you say you belonged to when you were a young woman in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Well - we didn't think about classes in those days. We - I think we were just ordinary brought up, homely and ther
e was no distinction, if you thought people you didn't know them and you didn't mix with them. You simply lived your lives at your own - home life together. There were no clubs or anything - people in those days. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 What sort of clubs do you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 For - people - the - there were no sort of clubs that people go to today, like they do today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 You mean like bingo and that kind of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh no nothing. Nothing.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 How were you taught to treat people, was there anybody you had to call sir or madam when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
No, not - not really. Vicars were the only people that were superior. Yes. The clergy. They ruled the law of the people and the young children and some used to bow to them. Yes. My sister - Hilda - no, not Hilda, Dol
l, the eldest one, she said, I'd never bow to any clergyman. She wouldn't. They - yes, used to curtsey in those days. There was that sort of - different - distinction.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did your mother bring you up to curtsey?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you ever curtsey?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 But other people did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Some did, some - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 What about your father, did he touch his cap?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Well - my father was just an ordinary working man, he went to work and he - just; came back you know an
d then if he wanted a glass of beer he had it in the evening sometimes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 In the pub or in his own home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 He had it - if he wanted to stop on his way home he'd get a glass of beer. And he had - always had some at home you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Do you remember anybody calling your mother madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did your mother have anything to do with people who were poorer than herself? Were there any people she helped with anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Well we didn't come in contact with them very much. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you at school a little bit, with poorer children?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 The poorer children seemed to keep to themselves. They didn't mix much you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 The poorer people, where did they live in those days in Colchester?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Well they lived - some down a - Priory Street and Stockwell Street. Then - we didn't -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Not round Hamilton Road then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
Oh no, not - no, they were all very decent people all round there. All working people but quiet you know and kept to themselves. Or homely people. Neighbours. Who helped one another.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
Do you remember when you were a child hearing people say that certain families were rough, do you remember that word being used about people, that they were rough?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh yes, I think there were rough people, who were very rough, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 What did they mean if they said rough in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
Well I suppose that meant that they hadn't much money and they lived in poor houses and hand't a lot of food and they - they were distinctions evidently but - amongst people but - like myself I didn't come - come in contact with them much. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Do you remember a distinction between craftsmen and labourers in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No, they worked together. I never heard the - there was any ructions with any of the workmen, they seemed to - all glad to w
ork and earn their money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 What about a man who had a trade, who was skilled?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
Well - no, I don't think they made a lot distinction. A headman seemed to fall in with all the - men and they were - didn't make any distinction in their working. My father didn't anyhow.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Do you remember if your father had any men friends that he brought to the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
Oh yes, he had several men friends. Yes, he - he used to do a lot of - he was very fond of greenhouse - and gardening and he - also had a piece 
of allotment and he had a pig. And of course Sundays they used to - friends used to come up and have a look at the garden and talk about these things you see. And that's they all talk - interested in - what they grew and what they did. Sort of homely affa
irs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Were their wives friends of the family too?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Not often. No. Not very often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Can you - remember any of these men and what jobs they did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Well - I - I think father had the men that worked for him. With him. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Were any of them also foremen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Well, mixed race, I don't think we took much notice of foremen and men then. Not really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 You think it's different now then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh yes. I think that more Miss Jones style today than there was then. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 You mentioned the kind of jumped up people were very different from the gentry in their manners and things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh yes, well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you meet those sort of people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 People - people - there wasn't that distinction in my young days. Not really, like - like it is today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 You said the people who thought they were better than other people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 There wasn't that style in - not in my day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 You don't remember those people in Colchester when you are a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No. No. No. The only thing - the businessmen were b
usinessmen and they - they were very different to what they - they were more sociable - by us then. Yes, more sociable. There wasn't that distinction.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 How did the businessmen behave then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh - well they always treated you - pleased to see you and I mean, serve you in shops and everything, they were - homely, very homely.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 When you say the businessmen you mean the shopkeepers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Shop - yes, all those businesses. Yes. Oh yes, they were quite homely and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Who did they associate with in their social life, who would their friends be, what sort of jobs would they have?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
Well in those days people seemed to live very quietly together, there wasn't a social life. There wasn't. No. There was no - no - everybody more or less stayed in 
their homes. And I think the only people who - went out were those who drank and went to public houses a lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you know any people like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Anybody round where you lived?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No. We were fairly quiet really. Because more or l
ess we were more a musical family and - had music and singing and mother used to sing - to us as children and all that sort of thing. Homely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Do you remember words like working class or poor class or lower class or upper class being used when you were a young person?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Well there wasn't - you didn't notice it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did your mother think of herself as belonging to a certain class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No. No. No, there was nothing like that when I - not when I was young.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 When do you think you first became conscious of this sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Well I think - we didn't notice it somehow, not - not - we weren't among the very poor people you see. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Do you think at that time it was possible to move from one class to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Well there wasn't that di
stinction. If anybody moved from a - a better house that what they're in, there was no - no Mr Jones's style with it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Do you remember anyone being described as a real gentleman or a real lady when you were a child or young girl?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Not in Colcheste
r. No, I think they were business men and ordinary people. The real - gentry either lived in the big houses away and you didn't come in contact. And there wasn't a great many round about here, not - they're farther away you see. From Colchester.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1449583\charrsid6895608 When you went to Melton Mowbr}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 ay there were the gentry there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 That was different altogether wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh - when I - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15757198 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
 and - and we had - when I went to London and mixed about there were the distinction then. More so which - people with money there. That was quite a different sort of - London's different.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Can you tell me how it was different, was everybody you met with money, would you call them all gentry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Well - well, no, you found a - real - gentry were those who'd go
t titles. And they - they were gentry because they were brought up to respect the servant. And there were a lot of servants in London. And the servants, well, they went to work and they had their time off an they just lived their lives. And the gentry - }
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1449583\charrsid6895608 well}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
 they lived their lives, they were off on certain things enjoying themselves I suppose and having dinner parties and - meetings. You didn't come into contact with that. You see, London life and country life is different - altogether.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 So in London you came in contact with the gentry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Because you were employed by them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 And you came in contact with their employees because you were an employee?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Were there any other people you met in London?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Well - never - I never - met - not anybody in ordinary stati}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1449583\charrsid6895608 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 n. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Just those two groups?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Just the that - high group people and - the servants. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you have any boyfriends when you were in London?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Not very much, no. I only met one policem
an. And when he - he was on duty, when I crossed the road and - I know - he - got - always used to make a friend - he did ask me to go out but I never went. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you want to go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No. Well I didn't know - I knew nothing about him you see, I wan
ted to know - like people's back - know all - more about them before - yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 So you didn't go out with anybody there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 When you were a child in Colchester do you remember seeing a policeman around where you lived?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No, I don't notice them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Do you remember anything about the police when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did your mother ever say, I'll call a policeman, if you were naughty?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Do you remember anything at all about the police?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No, I - I don't. I
 only know my brothers - used to - go and - and pick apples from somewhere and I just remember my mother saying, that you'll have the police after you and - of course the boys will be boys, they'll find them somewhere. But they never got into any really b
ad - trouble. No, not in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 That house you had in Gray Road, was it rented?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Rented.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Who was the landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 I can't -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you ever see him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No. No. The rent was paid through somebody else I think. I only know that my 
parents had the chance to buy the house, when the tenant - when the gentleman, whoever owned it, wanted to give it up but my father wouldn't enter any borrowing of money. Else we could have bought that house very reasonable.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Why did you move to that house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Well that house was sold.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Why did you first go to Gray Road when you were a little child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Because - my father was nearer his work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 That was when he moved to Mumfords?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Do you remember thinking that your parents had to struggle to make ends meet when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
Well they had to be careful with the large family. We never - there wasn't a struggle but they had to be careful. Yes, I don't think there was a lot of money wasted. But my mother was a very qui
et woman, she never complained. We always had good food, and we never went without.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Was your father ever ill or out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 So you never had to get any help from any outside?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang1034\langfe1033\langnp1034\insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang1034\langfe1033\langnp1034\insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No. No. No. No. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 I think in those days people helped each other more. If there was anybody who - a man or a woman ill there'd be one of neighbours come along and help you out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did your mother have a neighbour who helped ever?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Well - once side was an elderly lady and she had a maid to live with her. 
And the other side was a - an aunt who looked after the - two children and their parents were in service in Lexden Road.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Do you remember them ever helping your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No, I don't think we wanted any help really, not -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 If there was anybody round about who people disapproved of do you remember anyone ever making rough music?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Do you know what rough music was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No. No. I - no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 You never heard of that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No. No. Nothing of that. That was very - very quiet and - 
of course there wasn't much traffic and - no motor cars. Only horses and - and traps about.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Do you ever remember anybody - in Melton Mowbray do you remember anybody making a lot of tin cans?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No. No, it was very quiet - very nice little quiet place. No, there was nothing out of the ordinary there. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Do you remember any rough families there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
No. No. You were only friendly with - a shoemaker, shoeshop people. They had children and just see them and have a chat. And a - the shop we deal 
with where we - bought all our groceries. They were - no family there. So we were just ordinary people going from place to place.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 You were saying you were friendly with the shoemaker?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes, shoeshop people. Where we bought our shoes and - friendly with the - grocer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did they come to your house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
Well they - they - yes, they did but they always used to come - come in and have a chat. The schoolgirls and I remember the - other people used to call in the evening and we used to have friends in the evening for chats.;
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 That was the people who kept the shop was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 What about the schoolmaster, did he come in in the evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes, well, yes, my hubby used to see him occasionally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did he ever come in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes, he used to come in sometimes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Do you remember the vicar there or the director in Melton Mowbray?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
Not a lot, he was rather highbrow man. Yes. Cannon he was a canon there. Canon Wilberforce, I remember him. Yes, he didn't - he didn't call on people i
n those days. Well my husband being in the choir, of course, was with Sir Malcolm Sergeant all the time you see. And - he called in very often to see us.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did his father and mother live in the town?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No. I don't think so, I - I - I don't know whe
re. I know he lodged up very far from where we lived, in ordinary house with ordinary people. But I - don't know much about his parents.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 What was he like?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Quite homely little chap, nothing to look at, he was young then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 He was friendly was he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Very friendly. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 He'd come into your home would he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 When people came in was it for a meal or did they have just a cup of tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 When he came in - well, he didn't often come to any meals, he'd come in and sit down and have a little chat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 In the evening or the afternoon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
Sometimes during the daytime, sometimes in the evening. If he was passing by he call in. And the doctors, there were two doctors in Melton Mowbray, and they used to walk round the gardens 
and talk about the different things you see. Two; doctors in the village and a - yes, they were very homely and they used to like to walk round and - see the different things. The greenhouses, and - and all that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Were you friendly with anybody who was in service there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
No, I never - no, we didn't know - know the - in the big house, when they were there, I didn't know the servants 'cos I never went in the - the house while they were there. But while they were away there was a caretake, an old coup
le and then we used to go and see them. Like - the - the caretakers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 That was at Ashbury House was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes. No, Craven Lodge. That was Craven Lodge.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 In Melton Mowbray in the ordinary class of people have the same standard of living or would you say there were different groups?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
Well - we didn't know - we didn't know how they were place there. 'cos I don't think they were very well off, not really. We didn't come in contact with a lot of people there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Were there people there working a lot on farms, farmworkers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes. I should say so. Farms and - and - and horses. Lot of horses there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did they go to the mission church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Some of them did. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 There wasn't a chapel there was there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No, they didn't seem much to - this schoolmaster started this mission hall and - we used to have it every Sunday evening.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 The farmworkers there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 We had different people come.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Were you friendly with the farmworkers in a social way, or did you call on them and did they call on you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh yes, we - we knew several farm people out there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Farm labouerers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Well - the farm - the farmers themselves. We used to cycle out about a mile out to different farms my husband knew.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 But that was the people who owned the farms?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 What about the actual farm workers, the farm labourers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Well we didn't come in contact with them. No, not really. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 But they did attend the mission, you saw them there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Well - anybody came to the mission, they t
hought - the schoolmaster and the - used to tell the parents, the schoolteacher you see, and then the parents used to come.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 I wondered if the farm workers went to the mission or to the church?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Well some of them weren't near you see, they were - farms were a little farther away. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 You said your husband had about three pounds a week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
I think - I don't know whether - what it was - whether it was two or three, I forget. But it wasn't a great - great wage. I think it must have been about three.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you have a struggle to make ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
No. I had - I had no rent to pay. And - I had all vegetables and fruit I wanted. That - I didn't feel hard up because I - all I'd got to find was bread and meat and - that. Yes. In those days everything was so cheap you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Thinking about Melton Mowbray did your husband ever have anything to do with sport, did he watch football or cricket or play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No. No, not there, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 What about going fishing or shooting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No. No. No, he was - he was more or less garden.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Garden and his choir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
Yes. Oh - more or less 'cos I mean he had to tend to the glasshouses every night, and - keep the fire - see they had lights to keep going and - keep the heat on. Certain amount of heat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Do you ever remember a magic lantern show or a concert or anything of that sort of entertainment in Melton Mowbray?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No, there was nothing. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 If you went to visit people was it in the afternoon usually or in the evening after tea or when would you go and visit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Well - in the summertime we used to go on our cycle and cycle round.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 And have tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes. Yes. Call in a farmer's and - and have tea with there - some of the farmers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you belong to any societies or clubs or womens groups?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No. There was nothing like that. Clubs and - every entertainment, there was nothing in those days. You had to make your own enjoyment.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Do you know if your husband was ever a member of the Conservative party when you were in Melton Mowbray? Did he actually pay subscriptions?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 I don't think there was much - not of - not in that line, no. I don't remember him paying anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Do you remember him working for the party in an election?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No, he didn't do anything like that. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 You didn't distribute leaflets?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
No, I never - no, they didn't seem to have - meetings or anything, people just voted who they thought - there wasn't that - like it is today, people going round canvassing, no one to 
my knowledge ever canvassed. There was nothing like that. You - each one had their own idea what they voted - who they voted for.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did your husband ever argue about politics with anyone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No. No. 'Cos we agreed you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 You and he agreed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 But were any of your friends Liberals for example?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 We never talked about politics. Not in the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Do you know if any of his friends were Liberals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No, I never heard. It was so quiet everything then, they didn't get excited like they do today. We all get so excited over things now.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 The first time you had the vote would have been 1918, do you remember going to vote for the first time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 I can't remember. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Do you remember your husband going voting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No. No, I don't remember my first vote.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Do you remember in Melton Mowbray if there was a temperance club, anything to try and persuade people not to drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 I think there were - I believe there was something like that, but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Were you a member?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 I can't remember but I fancy there was - were temperance does about but I never was in contact with them. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 On Sundays in Melton Mowbray did your husband wear different clothes, did you and he wear different clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh yes, we always - always had different clothes Sundays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 What did he wear on a Sunday for going to church, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Well just another ordinary suit, he didn't have no tails or anything. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did he wear a hat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes. Trilby hat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you have special Sunday clothes too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
Yes. I had smart hat. I remember once going to church and there was some rooks up above. And - just as I got near they - they dropped down, I just nearly got caught. With the rooks from the trees. And I had a smart hat on. Oh it w
as a big hat in those times. With all pink roses all round. And I just escaped this - dropped from the trees.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 In those days was there anybody poaching round about in Melton Mowbray do you know, do you know if anybody poached game?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 You never heard about that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 You never got any meat from poaching?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you keep any hens or pigs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No. Nothing there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you make any wine or beer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you ever make any medicine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No. Nothing like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you ever bottle preserve fruit or vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh I made jams and - and that. Jam. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Your husband came home for midday meals did he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh he came in. He was on the spot you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 So he was there for all meals was he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 What time did you have breakfast when you were first }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15757198 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 I think we had it about eight o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Had he already been out to work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh yes, he used to getup and go out in the garden first thing. Then come in for breakfast. 
And of course he had the men there too, 'cos he had several men working with him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 They had the place where the gardeners used to train, was it called boffy or something?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh that - that's where they trained before you were head gardener.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 What was it like?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
Well it's just an ordinary - house where they had bedrooms I suppose, they had several bedrooms and room and a living room and then they - the men used to amuse theirselves in the evening playing cards and - music my husband had a conc
ertina and he used to play that in the goffy, but I didn't see it. This was all I heard.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Was he living there when he met you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Before he }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15757198 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 . When -

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Before his first marriage was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes. Before - yes, before he }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15757198 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608  he had to be trained. And that's the trained him - they go as men and they're trained in these places by the head gardener. And then they're trained 'til they're able to go out then on their own.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Was he trained at Croven Lodge?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No. He was trained - I think he was trained at - what's the name - forget the name.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Was it it Somerset?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 I forget the name of this - they were Jews. I've forgotten their name now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 When you had appendicitis you had a woman in to help you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No. There were no wome
n, the old lady used to come down from the big house and she used to - my hubby used to light the fire and - do that. And then - I got up and she helped like - we didn't have any people to help in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 This old lady who came down, who was she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 The caretaker up at the big house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 She used to come and help you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes. She used to come down and help me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 What did she do for you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh well, she used to - I think my hubby got the meal, I forget now, and - then she'd come up and 
tidy and light the fire you see. Then he'd come in and help, so one thing and another we managed I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did she come in quite often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Every day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh yes. Every day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you pay her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes, we gave her something and - oh yes, we gave her a little money but I for - forgotten what - in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 So you had some help anyway to help you when you were ill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh yes, yes, when I was - Yes, I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 What about washing, how did you manage with washing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 She - she used to do it. This old lady used to take it up - up the house and do it there. For about a twelve month I didn't do anything.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 She did it all for you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did your husband ask her to help or did you, how was it afranged?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 I think - I think between them they arranged that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Your husband and the woman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes. And she could spare the time then. She - well - getting on but she was pretty active.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 And she wasn't very busy at her own home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No, she was only caretaking you
 see, they only had their own room to do up and the bedroom to do up and just - look after the house, keep it aired.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did she cook the midday dinner then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Can't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Or did your husband or did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 I - I can't remember that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 I wondered if your husband ever did any cooking, you said he wasn't much of a cook?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No, he - he wasn't a cook.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 You don't remember who did the cooking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No, I can't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 You were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15757198 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
 in Colchester were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 About how many guests came to the wedding, was it just the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Just the family. Oh I suppose about a dozen of us, a few aunts and - uncles and cousins about.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you have a sort of party or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Just at home. And the curate
 came along I know. And he was very friendly man from the St Marys church. He came and had a meal with us and - my brother - Will at that time was in the church choir and - he was very friendly with him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did he do anything for the boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh yes, they did have a club.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did your brother go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes. Yes, my brothers used to go. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did you have a sort of tea or a meal at your home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh yes, we had quite a nice feast you know, extra, almost like we do now. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 The wedding was in the church was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes. Yes. Church wedding. And the curate - I had the curate because I knew him. He }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15757198 Married
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608  me. And then we went for our honeymoon to Goldhangar. And we went by carriers cart in that. Oh no, trap. Horse and trap. 'Course it was. A
nd then I stayed - we stayed there about a fortnight and then we went to Melton Mowbray afterwards.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did people throw confetti at you and that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 I think they did. I think they was all white - rice and stuff that time.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 You met your husband and started going out with him, did you have an engagement?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh yes, they have engagement ring.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 You were engaged?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Now long were you engaged?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Well I only knew him six months.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Were you engaged quite soon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh yes, soon - when - yes, he wanted to get }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15757198 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608  you see and - there was nothing to - stop him, he'd got his home you see. Quite a decent home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 How soon were you engaged after meeting him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Well - I suppose about a month or so. 'Cos we were young - weren't young you see, I was nearly thirty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 When you went away to be a nurse did this change your relationship with your mother and father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No, never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 You all felt the same?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes. There was no distinction whatever.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 What about with your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Oh they were all the same, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 It didn't make any difference?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No. I might have got a better - with being with gentry and people talking better, I might have really improved my speaking that way which
 has never left me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 You speak differently from Colchester people on the whole?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Yes. I - well I was, you see, away a number of years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Did people remark on it when you came back?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No. No. No, they - they didn't remark.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 When you came back to Colchester did it seem to you that other people spoke differently?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 
Well I noticed they were broader. Yes. Because some of the country people talk very broad in those days. I can remember they used to say, where are you going to boy? Like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 You don't hear it much now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5590480 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 No. All children educated different.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7233595 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12396363\charrsid6895608 Would you say that working full time changed your attitude to life in any way?
